{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W16eqZL6YUZaGriNeiWegj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Specification: 203 E2E Integration Tests\n     2→\n     3→## Meta\n     4→\n     5→| Field | Value |\n     6→|-------|-------|\n     7→| Status | Ready |\n     8→| Priority | P1 |\n     9→| Phase | 2 |\n    10→| NR_OF_TRIES | 7 |\n    11→\n    12→---\n    13→\n    14→## Overview\n    15→\n    16→End-to-end tests using Playwright that prove real transactions flow from the browser UI to on-chain programs and back. This spec defines two suites:\n    17→\n    18→1. **Local deterministic suite (`pnpm test:e2e`)** using `solana-test-validator` for fast CI gating.\n    19→2. **Devnet real-provider suite (`pnpm test:e2e:devnet`)** using deployed contracts and the real VRF provider.\n    20→\n    21→Both suites use the TestWalletProvider (from spec 205) to inject test keypairs and sign real transactions without a browser extension.\n    22→\n    23→## User Stories\n    24→\n    25→- As a developer, I want an E2E test that runs the full coinflip lifecycle (create → join → resolve → claim) through the real UI so that I know the frontend and on-chain programs work together.\n    26→- As a developer, I want E2E tests to catch regressions in the chain integration layer (chain.ts, CoinflipContext) that unit and component tests cannot.\n    27→- As a CI system, I want deterministic headless local E2E tests so that pull requests are gated on integration correctness.\n    28→- As a release system, I want real devnet + VRF E2E tests so that deployed contracts and provider callbacks are validated before release.\n    29→\n    30→---\n    31→\n    32→## Scope Alignment\n    33→\n    34→- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 9 (Quality & Testing)\n    35→- **Scope status**: V1 In Scope\n    36→- **Phase boundary**: Phase 2 — after wallet integration and component tests are stable\n    37→\n    38→## Required Context Files\n    39→\n    40→- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` — transaction builders\n    41→- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx` — game state\n    42→- `solana/programs/coinflip/` — on-chain program\n    43→- `solana/programs/platform/` — on-chain program\n    44→- `packages/wallet/src/` — TestWalletProvider (from spec 205)\n    45→\n    46→## Contract Files\n    47→\n    48→- `solana/tests/coinflip.ts` — bankrun tests define expected on-chain behavior\n    49→- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts` — UIMatch shape\n    50→\n    51→---\n    52→\n    53→## Functional Requirements\n    54→\n    55→### FR-1: Local Deterministic Infrastructure\n    56→\n    57→Set up the deterministic local E2E environment with Playwright and a local Solana validator.\n    58→\n    59→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    60→- [ ] Playwright configured for E2E tests (separate from visual regression config)\n    61→- [ ] Test setup script starts solana-test-validator with coinflip + platform programs deployed\n    62→- [ ] Local suite deploys programs as part of setup (blank chain; no pre-deployed assumption)\n    63→- [ ] Test setup airdrops SOL to test wallets\n    64→- [ ] App starts with VITE_RPC_URL pointing to local validator\n    65→- [ ] Test teardown stops the validator and cleans up\n    66→- [ ] E2E test command: `pnpm test:e2e`\n    67→\n    68→### FR-2: Coinflip Full Lifecycle\n    69→\n    70→Test the complete coinflip flow through the UI.\n    71→\n    72→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    73→- [ ] Test wallet A connects, navigates to /coinflip, selects a tier, picks Heads, creates a match\n    74→- [ ] Match appears in the open lobby\n    75→- [ ] Test wallet B connects (second browser context), sees the match, joins it\n    76→- [ ] Match transitions to locked phase in both contexts\n    77→- [ ] Oracle resolves the match (direct RPC call in test, not through UI)\n    78→- [ ] Winner sees \"You won\" result, loser sees \"You lost\"\n    79→- [ ] Winner claims payout, balance increases by expected amount (pool minus 3% fee)\n    80→- [ ] Match disappears from lobby after claim\n    81→\n    82→### FR-3: Cancel Flow\n    83→\n    84→Test match cancellation.\n    85→\n    86→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    87→- [ ] Creator creates a match, then cancels before anyone joins\n    88→- [ ] Creator's balance is refunded (entry amount + rent)\n    89→- [ ] Match disappears from the lobby\n    90→- [ ] Creator can create a new match after cancellation\n    91→\n    92→### FR-4: Error Scenarios\n    93→\n    94→Test that error states surface correctly in the UI.\n    95→\n    96→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    97→- [ ] Creating a match with insufficient balance shows an error message\n    98→- [ ] Joining an already-locked match shows an error message\n    99→- [ ] Claiming as the loser shows an error message\n   100→\n   101→### FR-5: On-Chain State Verification\n   102→\n   103→Local deterministic tests must verify on-chain state, not just UI state.\n   104→\n   105→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   106→- [ ] After match creation, test queries the match PDA and verifies account data\n   107→- [ ] After claim, test verifies the match account is closed\n   108→- [ ] After claim, test verifies treasury received the fee\n   109→- [ ] After claim, test verifies player profiles are updated (totalGames, wins)\n   110→\n   111→### FR-6: Devnet Real VRF Integration\n   112→\n   113→Run E2E tests against deployed devnet contracts and the real VRF provider.\n   114→\n   115→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   116→- [ ] Separate Playwright project/config for devnet suite (not sharing local validator setup)\n   117→- [ ] App runs against devnet RPC with deployed coinflip/platform program IDs\n   118→- [ ] Devnet suite does not deploy contracts; it fails fast if required deployed IDs/env are missing\n   119→- [ ] Test triggers real VRF request path (no local mock resolve shortcut)\n   120→- [ ] Test waits for real provider callback/fulfillment and asserts resolved winner/loser UI state\n   121→- [ ] Winner claim succeeds and on-chain account/balance outcomes are verified on devnet\n   122→- [ ] Test command: `pnpm test:e2e:devnet`\n   123→- [ ] Suite includes retry/poll strategy and explicit timeout budget for async fulfillment\n   124→\n   125→---\n   126→\n   127→## Success Criteria\n   128→\n   129→- Local lifecycle suite passes end-to-end in under 60 seconds\n   130→- Local suite is deterministic (same result on every run)\n   131→- Devnet suite passes against deployed contracts with real VRF fulfillment\n   132→- No browser extension required (TestWalletProvider handles signing)\n   133→- On-chain state matches expected values after each step in both suites\n   134→\n   135→---\n   136→\n   137→## Dependencies\n   138→\n   139→- Spec 205 (Real Wallet) — TestWalletProvider must exist\n   140→- Spec 200 (Visual Regression) — Playwright already installed\n   141→- solana-test-validator available in CI environment\n   142→- Programs compiled and deployable (`anchor build`)\n   143→- Devnet contracts deployed and environment variables documented for program IDs\n   144→- Real VRF provider credentials/configuration available in devnet environment\n   145→\n   146→## Assumptions\n   147→\n   148→- Two browser contexts simulate two different players\n   149→- Local suite triggers resolution programmatically in tests (not through UI) for determinism\n   150→- Devnet suite uses real VRF request/fulfillment path\n   151→- Test validator starts fresh for each local test suite (clean state)\n   152→- Airdrop is available on test validator (not rate-limited)\n   153→\n   154→---\n   155→\n   156→## Validation Plan\n   157→\n   158→| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n   159→|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n   160→| 1 | Local lifecycle passes | `pnpm test:e2e` output | Green local run |\n   161→| 2 | Local on-chain state correct | Local RPC queries in test assertions | Account data matches |\n   162→| 3 | Local deterministic | Run local suite 3 times consecutively | All pass |\n   163→| 4 | Local under 60 seconds | Time local test run | Timing output |\n   164→| 5 | Devnet VRF path passes | `pnpm test:e2e:devnet` output | Green devnet run |\n   165→| 6 | Devnet fulfillment observed | Poll + assertion logs in test output | VRF callback evidence |\n   166→\n   167→---\n   168→\n   169→## Completion Signal\n   170→\n   171→### Implementation Checklist\n   172→- [x] [test] Baseline Playwright real-mode config and smoke spec exist (`playwright.real.config.ts`, `e2e/real/startup.spec.ts`) (done: prior specs)\n   173→- [x] [test] Add dedicated local E2E Playwright project/config (`e2e/local/**`) separated from visual and real-wallet smoke tests (done: iteration 1)\n   174→- [x] [test] Create localnet bootstrap script: start fresh `solana-test-validator`, deploy coinflip + platform programs, wait for RPC readiness (done: iteration 2)\n   175→- [x] [test] Create localnet teardown script: stop validator process, clean temp ledger/logs, and guarantee cleanup on test failure (done: iteration 3)\n   176→- [x] [test] Add deterministic wallet-funding helper (airdrop + confirm) for both test players before each local suite run (done: iteration 4)\n   177→- [x] [test] Add shared E2E helpers: selectors/page-object methods for create, join, claim, cancel, and reusable wait/assert primitives (done: iteration 5)\n   178→- [x] [test] Add shared on-chain assertion helpers for match PDA state, treasury fee delta, and player profile stat updates (done: iteration 6)\n   179→- [x] [test] Add dual-browser-context fixture with isolated storage/session for player A and player B (done: iteration 7)\n   180→- [ ] [test] Implement local lifecycle test (create -> join -> resolve programmatically -> claim) with UI assertions in both contexts\n   181→- [ ] [test] Implement local lifecycle on-chain assertions (match state after create, closed after claim, fee + profile invariants)\n   182→- [ ] [test] Implement local cancel-flow test (create -> cancel -> refund verified -> lobby clears -> recreate works)\n   183→- [ ] [test] Implement local error-flow tests (insufficient balance, join locked match, loser claim attempt)\n   184→- [ ] [test] Add local suite command `pnpm test:e2e` that runs bootstrap -> tests -> teardown in one entrypoint\n   185→- [ ] [test] Add devnet env contract (required vars + validation): RPC URL, coinflip/platform program IDs, VRF config; fail fast if missing\n   186→- [ ] [test] Add dedicated devnet E2E Playwright project/config (`e2e/devnet/**`) that does not run local bootstrap/deploy\n   187→- [ ] [test] Implement devnet lifecycle test using deployed contracts + real VRF request/fulfillment path (no mock resolve shortcut)\n   188→- [ ] [test] Add robust fulfillment polling/backoff + timeout budget in devnet test, with tx signature logging for failures\n   189→- [ ] [test] Add devnet on-chain assertions for payout, fee transfer, and final match/account state\n   190→- [ ] [test] Add devnet suite command `pnpm test:e2e:devnet` wired to the devnet project/config\n   191→- [ ] [test] Prove local determinism by running `pnpm test:e2e` three consecutive times (all pass, stable assertions)\n   192→- [ ] [test] Record local runtime evidence (<60s target) and devnet real-VRF pass evidence in test output artifacts/logs\n   193→- [x] [test] Visual regression baseline updates are not required for this spec (test infra + assertions only; no intended UI redesign)\n   194→\n   195→### Testing Requirements\n   196→\n   197→The agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n   198→\n   199→#### Code Quality\n   200→- [ ] All existing tests pass\n   201→- [ ] Local E2E tests pass (`pnpm test:e2e`)\n   202→- [ ] Devnet E2E tests pass (`pnpm test:e2e:devnet`) in designated environment\n   203→- [ ] No lint errors\n   204→\n   205→#### Functional Verification\n   206→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n   207→- [ ] Local tests are deterministic (3 consecutive runs pass)\n   208→- [ ] Devnet test demonstrates real VRF request-to-fulfillment path\n   209→\n   210→#### Visual Verification (if UI)\n   211→- [ ] N/A (E2E tests verify behavior, not appearance)\n   212→\n   213→#### Console/Network Check (if web)\n   214→- [ ] No unhandled JS console errors during E2E runs\n   215→- [ ] All RPC requests succeed\n   216→\n   217→### Iteration Instructions\n   218→\n   219→If ANY check fails:\n   220→1. Identify the specific issue\n   221→2. Fix the code\n   222→3. Re-run tests\n   223→4. Re-verify all criteria\n   224→5. Check again\n   225→\n   226→**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n   227→\n   228→### Post-Completion: Gap Analysis\n   229→\n   230→After the spec loop outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`, `spec-loop.sh` automatically runs\n   231→`/gap-analysis {id} --non-interactive` which:\n   232→1. Audits every FR acceptance criterion against the codebase\n   233→2. Writes `docs/specs/{id}/gap-analysis.md` with inventory + audit + recommendations\n   234→3. Annotates FR checkboxes with HTML comment evidence (`<!-- satisfied: ... -->`)\n   235→4. Commits everything together with the completion commit\n   236→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b0a0dcb3-1758-4eec-aea3-903a9f33143b","uuid":"ebed1a8a-9b42-47a5-9916-d14d6a892fbf","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/203-e2e-integration/spec.md","content":"# Specification: 203 E2E Integration Tests\n\n## Meta\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Status | Ready |\n| Priority | P1 |\n| Phase | 2 |\n| NR_OF_TRIES | 7 |\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nEnd-to-end tests using Playwright that prove real transactions flow from the browser UI to on-chain programs and back. This spec defines two suites:\n\n1. **Local deterministic suite (`pnpm test:e2e`)** using `solana-test-validator` for fast CI gating.\n2. **Devnet real-provider suite (`pnpm test:e2e:devnet`)** using deployed contracts and the real VRF provider.\n\nBoth suites use the TestWalletProvider (from spec 205) to inject test keypairs and sign real transactions without a browser extension.\n\n## User Stories\n\n- As a developer, I want an E2E test that runs the full coinflip lifecycle (create → join → resolve → claim) through the real UI so that I know the frontend and on-chain programs work together.\n- As a developer, I want E2E tests to catch regressions in the chain integration layer (chain.ts, CoinflipContext) that unit and component tests cannot.\n- As a CI system, I want deterministic headless local E2E tests so that pull requests are gated on integration correctness.\n- As a release system, I want real devnet + VRF E2E tests so that deployed contracts and provider callbacks are validated before release.\n\n---\n\n## Scope Alignment\n\n- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 9 (Quality & Testing)\n- **Scope status**: V1 In Scope\n- **Phase boundary**: Phase 2 — after wallet integration and component tests are stable\n\n## Required Context Files\n\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` — transaction builders\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx` — game state\n- `solana/programs/coinflip/` — on-chain program\n- `solana/programs/platform/` — on-chain program\n- `packages/wallet/src/` — TestWalletProvider (from spec 205)\n\n## Contract Files\n\n- `solana/tests/coinflip.ts` — bankrun tests define expected on-chain behavior\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts` — UIMatch shape\n\n---\n\n## Functional Requirements\n\n### FR-1: Local Deterministic Infrastructure\n\nSet up the deterministic local E2E environment with Playwright and a local Solana validator.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Playwright configured for E2E tests (separate from visual regression config)\n- [ ] Test setup script starts solana-test-validator with coinflip + platform programs deployed\n- [ ] Local suite deploys programs as part of setup (blank chain; no pre-deployed assumption)\n- [ ] Test setup airdrops SOL to test wallets\n- [ ] App starts with VITE_RPC_URL pointing to local validator\n- [ ] Test teardown stops the validator and cleans up\n- [ ] E2E test command: `pnpm test:e2e`\n\n### FR-2: Coinflip Full Lifecycle\n\nTest the complete coinflip flow through the UI.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Test wallet A connects, navigates to /coinflip, selects a tier, picks Heads, creates a match\n- [ ] Match appears in the open lobby\n- [ ] Test wallet B connects (second browser context), sees the match, joins it\n- [ ] Match transitions to locked phase in both contexts\n- [ ] Oracle resolves the match (direct RPC call in test, not through UI)\n- [ ] Winner sees \"You won\" result, loser sees \"You lost\"\n- [ ] Winner claims payout, balance increases by expected amount (pool minus 3% fee)\n- [ ] Match disappears from lobby after claim\n\n### FR-3: Cancel Flow\n\nTest match cancellation.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Creator creates a match, then cancels before anyone joins\n- [ ] Creator's balance is refunded (entry amount + rent)\n- [ ] Match disappears from the lobby\n- [ ] Creator can create a new match after cancellation\n\n### FR-4: Error Scenarios\n\nTest that error states surface correctly in the UI.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Creating a match with insufficient balance shows an error message\n- [ ] Joining an already-locked match shows an error message\n- [ ] Claiming as the loser shows an error message\n\n### FR-5: On-Chain State Verification\n\nLocal deterministic tests must verify on-chain state, not just UI state.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] After match creation, test queries the match PDA and verifies account data\n- [ ] After claim, test verifies the match account is closed\n- [ ] After claim, test verifies treasury received the fee\n- [ ] After claim, test verifies player profiles are updated (totalGames, wins)\n\n### FR-6: Devnet Real VRF Integration\n\nRun E2E tests against deployed devnet contracts and the real VRF provider.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Separate Playwright project/config for devnet suite (not sharing local validator setup)\n- [ ] App runs against devnet RPC with deployed coinflip/platform program IDs\n- [ ] Devnet suite does not deploy contracts; it fails fast if required deployed IDs/env are missing\n- [ ] Test triggers real VRF request path (no local mock resolve shortcut)\n- [ ] Test waits for real provider callback/fulfillment and asserts resolved winner/loser UI state\n- [ ] Winner claim succeeds and on-chain account/balance outcomes are verified on devnet\n- [ ] Test command: `pnpm test:e2e:devnet`\n- [ ] Suite includes retry/poll strategy and explicit timeout budget for async fulfillment\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Local lifecycle suite passes end-to-end in under 60 seconds\n- Local suite is deterministic (same result on every run)\n- Devnet suite passes against deployed contracts with real VRF fulfillment\n- No browser extension required (TestWalletProvider handles signing)\n- On-chain state matches expected values after each step in both suites\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Spec 205 (Real Wallet) — TestWalletProvider must exist\n- Spec 200 (Visual Regression) — Playwright already installed\n- solana-test-validator available in CI environment\n- Programs compiled and deployable (`anchor build`)\n- Devnet contracts deployed and environment variables documented for program IDs\n- Real VRF provider credentials/configuration available in devnet environment\n\n## Assumptions\n\n- Two browser contexts simulate two different players\n- Local suite triggers resolution programmatically in tests (not through UI) for determinism\n- Devnet suite uses real VRF request/fulfillment path\n- Test validator starts fresh for each local test suite (clean state)\n- Airdrop is available on test validator (not rate-limited)\n\n---\n\n## Validation Plan\n\n| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n| 1 | Local lifecycle passes | `pnpm test:e2e` output | Green local run |\n| 2 | Local on-chain state correct | Local RPC queries in test assertions | Account data matches |\n| 3 | Local deterministic | Run local suite 3 times consecutively | All pass |\n| 4 | Local under 60 seconds | Time local test run | Timing output |\n| 5 | Devnet VRF path passes | `pnpm test:e2e:devnet` output | Green devnet run |\n| 6 | Devnet fulfillment observed | Poll + assertion logs in test output | VRF callback evidence |\n\n---\n\n## Completion Signal\n\n### Implementation Checklist\n- [x] [test] Baseline Playwright real-mode config and smoke spec exist (`playwright.real.config.ts`, `e2e/real/startup.spec.ts`) (done: prior specs)\n- [x] [test] Add dedicated local E2E Playwright project/config (`e2e/local/**`) separated from visual and real-wallet smoke tests (done: iteration 1)\n- [x] [test] Create localnet bootstrap script: start fresh `solana-test-validator`, deploy coinflip + platform programs, wait for RPC readiness (done: iteration 2)\n- [x] [test] Create localnet teardown script: stop validator process, clean temp ledger/logs, and guarantee cleanup on test failure (done: iteration 3)\n- [x] [test] Add deterministic wallet-funding helper (airdrop + confirm) for both test players before each local suite run (done: iteration 4)\n- [x] [test] Add shared E2E helpers: selectors/page-object methods for create, join, claim, cancel, and reusable wait/assert primitives (done: iteration 5)\n- [x] [test] Add shared on-chain assertion helpers for match PDA state, treasury fee delta, and player profile stat updates (done: iteration 6)\n- [x] [test] Add dual-browser-context fixture with isolated storage/session for player A and player B (done: iteration 7)\n- [ ] [test] Implement local lifecycle test (create -> join -> resolve programmatically -> claim) with UI assertions in both contexts\n- [ ] [test] Implement local lifecycle on-chain assertions (match state after create, closed after claim, fee + profile invariants)\n- [ ] [test] Implement local cancel-flow test (create -> cancel -> refund verified -> lobby clears -> recreate works)\n- [ ] [test] Implement local error-flow tests (insufficient balance, join locked match, loser claim attempt)\n- [ ] [test] Add local suite command `pnpm test:e2e` that runs bootstrap -> tests -> teardown in one entrypoint\n- [ ] [test] Add devnet env contract (required vars + validation): RPC URL, coinflip/platform program IDs, VRF config; fail fast if missing\n- [ ] [test] Add dedicated devnet E2E Playwright project/config (`e2e/devnet/**`) that does not run local bootstrap/deploy\n- [ ] [test] Implement devnet lifecycle test using deployed contracts + real VRF request/fulfillment path (no mock resolve shortcut)\n- [ ] [test] Add robust fulfillment polling/backoff + timeout budget in devnet test, with tx signature logging for failures\n- [ ] [test] Add devnet on-chain assertions for payout, fee transfer, and final match/account state\n- [ ] [test] Add devnet suite command `pnpm test:e2e:devnet` wired to the devnet project/config\n- [ ] [test] Prove local determinism by running `pnpm test:e2e` three consecutive times (all pass, stable assertions)\n- [ ] [test] Record local runtime evidence (<60s target) and devnet real-VRF pass evidence in test output artifacts/logs\n- [x] [test] Visual regression baseline updates are not required for this spec (test infra + assertions only; no intended UI redesign)\n\n### Testing Requirements\n\nThe agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n\n#### Code Quality\n- [ ] All existing tests pass\n- [ ] Local E2E tests pass (`pnpm test:e2e`)\n- [ ] Devnet E2E tests pass (`pnpm test:e2e:devnet`) in designated environment\n- [ ] No lint errors\n\n#### Functional Verification\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n- [ ] Local tests are deterministic (3 consecutive runs pass)\n- [ ] Devnet test demonstrates real VRF request-to-fulfillment path\n\n#### Visual Verification (if UI)\n- [ ] N/A (E2E tests verify behavior, not appearance)\n\n#### Console/Network Check (if web)\n- [ ] No unhandled JS console errors during E2E runs\n- [ ] All RPC requests succeed\n\n### Iteration Instructions\n\nIf ANY check fails:\n1. Identify the specific issue\n2. Fix the code\n3. Re-run tests\n4. Re-verify all criteria\n5. Check again\n\n**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n\n### Post-Completion: Gap Analysis\n\nAfter the spec loop outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`, `spec-loop.sh` automatically runs\n`/gap-analysis {id} --non-interactive` which:\n1. Audits every FR acceptance criterion against the codebase\n2. Writes `docs/specs/{id}/gap-analysis.md` with inventory + audit + recommendations\n3. Annotates FR checkboxes with HTML comment evidence (`<!-- satisfied: ... -->`)\n4. Commits everything together with the completion commit\n","numLines":236,"startLine":1,"totalLines":236}}}
