{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HPYnWHhJrL4KCbn4H8ioP8","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've successfully retrieved all five files in full. Here's a summary of the E2E testing API surface available:\n\n---\n\n## E2E Testing API Summary\n\n### 1. **fixtures.ts** - Dual Browser Context Setup\nProvides a Playwright test extension with isolated browser contexts for two players:\n\n**Fixtures exposed:**\n- `playerAPage` / `playerBPage` — Independent browser pages with deterministic keypairs\n- `playerAContext` / `playerBContext` — Isolated browser contexts\n- `playerAKeypair` / `playerBKeypair` — Deterministic keypair objects\n- `connection` — Shared RPC connection to local validator\n\n**Key mechanism:** Uses `addInitScript()` to inject a wallet seed (`__TEST_WALLET_SEED__`) into each context before page loads, enabling the TestWalletProvider to auto-derive the correct keypair.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **wallets.ts** - Wallet Funding Helpers\nUtilities for deterministic wallet creation and on-chain funding:\n\n**Keypairs:**\n- `PLAYER_A` — Deterministic keypair from seed `0xaa...` (32 bytes)\n- `PLAYER_B` — Deterministic keypair from seed `0xbb...` (32 bytes)\n\n**Functions:**\n- `fundWallet(connection, to, solAmount?)` — Airdrop SOL to a wallet (default 10 SOL) and confirm\n- `fundTestWallets(rpcUrl?, solAmount?)` — Fund both players, verify balances, return keypairs + connection\n\n---\n\n### 3. **page-objects.ts** - UI Interaction Helpers\nCSS-class-based selectors and action wrappers for coinflip gameplay:\n\n**Navigation & Setup:**\n- `navigateToCoinflip(page)` — Go to `/coinflip`, wait for lobby to render\n- `selectTier(page, tier)` — Select a tier (iron, bronze, silver, gold, platinum, diamond)\n- `selectSide(page, side)` — Select heads or tails\n\n**Gameplay Actions:**\n- `createMatch(page, tier, side)` — Create a game, wait for active match (waiting state)\n- `joinMatch(page, matchIndex?)` — Join the first (or specific) joinable match\n- `cancelMatch(page)` — Cancel an active match in waiting phase\n- `claimOrSettle(page)` — Claim payout (winner) or settle (loser)\n- `backToLobby(page)` — Return to lobby after claim\n\n**Wait / Assert Primitives:**\n- `waitForPhaseLabel(page, label, timeout?)` — Wait for sidebar status text (e.g., \"Waiting...\", \"Flipping...\")\n- `waitForResult(page, timeout?)` — Wait for win/loss outcome, returns \"won\" | \"lost\"\n- `waitForLobbyMatch(page, timeout?)` — Wait for a match to appear in lobby\n- `waitForLobby(page, timeout?)` — Wait for lobby to be visible\n- `waitForText(page, text, timeout?)` — Wait for text anywhere on page\n\n**Assertions:**\n- `assertLobbyEmpty(page, timeout?)` — Verify no open matches\n- `assertErrorToast(page, messageSubstring, timeout?)` — Verify error message visible\n- `assertNoErrorToast(page)` — Verify no error toasts present\n\n**Utilities:**\n- `getSolBalance(page, walletAddress, rpcUrl?)` — Fetch wallet balance via RPC from browser\n- `trackConsoleErrors(page)` — Collect browser console errors, returns `errors[]` + `assertClean()`\n\n**Selector object** (`sel`) — All CSS class selectors used throughout coinflip UI\n\n---\n\n### 4. **on-chain.ts** - On-Chain Assertions & RPC Queries\nAnchor-based helpers for querying and asserting match state, fees, and player profiles:\n\n**Program Instances:**\n- `getCoinflipProgram(connection)` — Returns a read-only Anchor Program<Coinflip>\n- `getPlatformProgram(connection)` — Returns a read-only Anchor Program<Platform>\n\n**PDA Derivation:**\n- `getMatchPda(creator)` — Derive match PDA for a creator\n- `getConfigPda()` — Derive coinflip config PDA\n- `getPlayerProfilePda(wallet)` — Derive player profile PDA\n\n**Account Fetching:**\n- `fetchMatch(connection, matchPda)` — Fetch match account, returns `MatchAccount | null`\n- `fetchPlayerProfile(connection, profilePda)` — Fetch player profile, returns `PlayerProfileAccount | null`\n- `getTreasuryAddress(connection)` — Fetch treasury wallet from coinflip config\n\n**Balance & Snapshots:**\n- `getBalanceLamports(connection, address)` — Get SOL balance in lamports\n- `snapshotBalance(connection, address)` — Snapshot balance for later delta comparison\n- `snapshotPlayerProfile(connection, wallet)` — Snapshot profile stats (or return zeros if not created)\n\n**Fee Calculation:**\n- `calculateExpectedFee(entryAmount)` — Calculate pool, fee (300 bps), and net payout in lamports\n\n**Assertion Functions:**\n- `assertMatchCreated(connection, creator, expectedTier, expectedSide)` — Verify match PDA in waiting phase\n- `assertMatchClosed(connection, matchPda)` — Verify match PDA is closed\n- `assertTreasuryFee(connection, treasury, balanceBefore, entryAmount)` — Verify treasury received expected fee\n- `assertPlayerProfile(connection, wallet, expected)` — Assert exact profile stat values\n- `assertPlayerProfileDelta(connection, wallet, before, delta)` — Assert profile stats changed by expected deltas\n\n**Account Type Interfaces:**\n- `MatchAccount` — match creator, opponent, tier, phase, winner, claimed, timestamps, VRF key, etc.\n- `PlayerProfileAccount` — authority, totalGames, wins, totalWagered, totalWon, bump\n\n---\n\n### 5. **playwright.local.config.ts** - Test Configuration\nPlaywright config for local integration tests:\n\n**Key settings:**\n- `testDir: \"./e2e\"` — Test directory\n- `testMatch: \"local/**/*.spec.ts\"` — Test file pattern\n- `baseURL: \"http://localhost:3002\"` — Frontend URL\n- `workers: 1, fullyParallel: false` — Sequential test execution\n- `timeout: 60_000` — 60s per test\n- `viewport: 1280 × 1080` — Desktop Chrome\n\n**Dev server (Vite):**\n- Starts at `http://localhost:3002` on port 3002\n- Environment variables:\n  - `VITE_MOCK_MODE=false` — Use real wallet\n  - `VITE_TEST_WALLET=true` — Enable TestWalletProvider (reads `__TEST_WALLET_SEED__`)\n  - `VITE_RPC_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8899` — Local validator\n  - `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK=localnet` — Network mode\n\n---\n\n## Typical Test Pattern\n\n```typescript\nimport { test, expect } from \"./fixtures\";\nimport * as po from \"./helpers/page-objects\";\nimport * as onChain from \"./helpers/on-chain\";\nimport { fundTestWallets } from \"./helpers/wallets\";\n\ntest.beforeAll(async () => {\n  await fundTestWallets(); // Airdrop SOL\n});\n\ntest(\"full game flow\", async ({ playerAPage, playerBPage, playerAKeypair, playerBKeypair, connection }) => {\n  // Navigate both players to coinflip\n  await po.navigateToCoinflip(playerAPage);\n  await po.navigateToCoinflip(playerBPage);\n\n  // Player A creates a game\n  await po.createMatch(playerAPage, \"iron\", \"heads\");\n\n  // Verify on-chain state\n  const { matchPda } = await onChain.assertMatchCreated(\n    connection,\n    playerAKeypair.publicKey,\n    0, // tier 0 = iron\n    0, // side 0 = heads\n  );\n\n  // Player B joins\n  await po.joinMatch(playerBPage);\n\n  // Wait for game to resolve\n  const resultA = await po.waitForResult(playerAPage);\n  const resultB = await po.waitForResult(playerBPage);\n\n  // Claim payouts\n  await po.claimOrSettle(playerAPage);\n  await po.claimOrSettle(playerBPage);\n\n  // Verify on-chain: match closed, treasury received fee, profiles updated\n  await onChain.assertMatchClosed(connection, matchPda);\n  // ... assert treasury fee, player profiles\n});\n```\n\nAll files are comprehensive and ready to use for writing integration tests!"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a6ce6323b44fee699 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 41739\ntool_uses: 5\nduration_ms: 23513</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b0a0dcb3-1758-4eec-aea3-903a9f33143b","uuid":"1540ebf0-62d7-439e-8d3a-57b09c6bff26","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read these files and return their FULL contents. I need to understand the APIs available for writing E2E tests:\n\n1. `apps/platform/e2e/local/fixtures.ts` - dual-browser-context fixture\n2. `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts` - wallet funding helpers\n3. `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/page-objects.ts` - page object methods\n4. `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/on-chain.ts` - on-chain assertion helpers\n5. `apps/platform/playwright.local.config.ts` - playwright config\n\nAll paths relative to `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/`\n\nReturn the COMPLETE content of each file.","agentId":"a6ce6323b44fee699","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've successfully retrieved all five files in full. Here's a summary of the E2E testing API surface available:\n\n---\n\n## E2E Testing API Summary\n\n### 1. **fixtures.ts** - Dual Browser Context Setup\nProvides a Playwright test extension with isolated browser contexts for two players:\n\n**Fixtures exposed:**\n- `playerAPage` / `playerBPage` — Independent browser pages with deterministic keypairs\n- `playerAContext` / `playerBContext` — Isolated browser contexts\n- `playerAKeypair` / `playerBKeypair` — Deterministic keypair objects\n- `connection` — Shared RPC connection to local validator\n\n**Key mechanism:** Uses `addInitScript()` to inject a wallet seed (`__TEST_WALLET_SEED__`) into each context before page loads, enabling the TestWalletProvider to auto-derive the correct keypair.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **wallets.ts** - Wallet Funding Helpers\nUtilities for deterministic wallet creation and on-chain funding:\n\n**Keypairs:**\n- `PLAYER_A` — Deterministic keypair from seed `0xaa...` (32 bytes)\n- `PLAYER_B` — Deterministic keypair from seed `0xbb...` (32 bytes)\n\n**Functions:**\n- `fundWallet(connection, to, solAmount?)` — Airdrop SOL to a wallet (default 10 SOL) and confirm\n- `fundTestWallets(rpcUrl?, solAmount?)` — Fund both players, verify balances, return keypairs + connection\n\n---\n\n### 3. **page-objects.ts** - UI Interaction Helpers\nCSS-class-based selectors and action wrappers for coinflip gameplay:\n\n**Navigation & Setup:**\n- `navigateToCoinflip(page)` — Go to `/coinflip`, wait for lobby to render\n- `selectTier(page, tier)` — Select a tier (iron, bronze, silver, gold, platinum, diamond)\n- `selectSide(page, side)` — Select heads or tails\n\n**Gameplay Actions:**\n- `createMatch(page, tier, side)` — Create a game, wait for active match (waiting state)\n- `joinMatch(page, matchIndex?)` — Join the first (or specific) joinable match\n- `cancelMatch(page)` — Cancel an active match in waiting phase\n- `claimOrSettle(page)` — Claim payout (winner) or settle (loser)\n- `backToLobby(page)` — Return to lobby after claim\n\n**Wait / Assert Primitives:**\n- `waitForPhaseLabel(page, label, timeout?)` — Wait for sidebar status text (e.g., \"Waiting...\", \"Flipping...\")\n- `waitForResult(page, timeout?)` — Wait for win/loss outcome, returns \"won\" | \"lost\"\n- `waitForLobbyMatch(page, timeout?)` — Wait for a match to appear in lobby\n- `waitForLobby(page, timeout?)` — Wait for lobby to be visible\n- `waitForText(page, text, timeout?)` — Wait for text anywhere on page\n\n**Assertions:**\n- `assertLobbyEmpty(page, timeout?)` — Verify no open matches\n- `assertErrorToast(page, messageSubstring, timeout?)` — Verify error message visible\n- `assertNoErrorToast(page)` — Verify no error toasts present\n\n**Utilities:**\n- `getSolBalance(page, walletAddress, rpcUrl?)` — Fetch wallet balance via RPC from browser\n- `trackConsoleErrors(page)` — Collect browser console errors, returns `errors[]` + `assertClean()`\n\n**Selector object** (`sel`) — All CSS class selectors used throughout coinflip UI\n\n---\n\n### 4. **on-chain.ts** - On-Chain Assertions & RPC Queries\nAnchor-based helpers for querying and asserting match state, fees, and player profiles:\n\n**Program Instances:**\n- `getCoinflipProgram(connection)` — Returns a read-only Anchor Program<Coinflip>\n- `getPlatformProgram(connection)` — Returns a read-only Anchor Program<Platform>\n\n**PDA Derivation:**\n- `getMatchPda(creator)` — Derive match PDA for a creator\n- `getConfigPda()` — Derive coinflip config PDA\n- `getPlayerProfilePda(wallet)` — Derive player profile PDA\n\n**Account Fetching:**\n- `fetchMatch(connection, matchPda)` — Fetch match account, returns `MatchAccount | null`\n- `fetchPlayerProfile(connection, profilePda)` — Fetch player profile, returns `PlayerProfileAccount | null`\n- `getTreasuryAddress(connection)` — Fetch treasury wallet from coinflip config\n\n**Balance & Snapshots:**\n- `getBalanceLamports(connection, address)` — Get SOL balance in lamports\n- `snapshotBalance(connection, address)` — Snapshot balance for later delta comparison\n- `snapshotPlayerProfile(connection, wallet)` — Snapshot profile stats (or return zeros if not created)\n\n**Fee Calculation:**\n- `calculateExpectedFee(entryAmount)` — Calculate pool, fee (300 bps), and net payout in lamports\n\n**Assertion Functions:**\n- `assertMatchCreated(connection, creator, expectedTier, expectedSide)` — Verify match PDA in waiting phase\n- `assertMatchClosed(connection, matchPda)` — Verify match PDA is closed\n- `assertTreasuryFee(connection, treasury, balanceBefore, entryAmount)` — Verify treasury received expected fee\n- `assertPlayerProfile(connection, wallet, expected)` — Assert exact profile stat values\n- `assertPlayerProfileDelta(connection, wallet, before, delta)` — Assert profile stats changed by expected deltas\n\n**Account Type Interfaces:**\n- `MatchAccount` — match creator, opponent, tier, phase, winner, claimed, timestamps, VRF key, etc.\n- `PlayerProfileAccount` — authority, totalGames, wins, totalWagered, totalWon, bump\n\n---\n\n### 5. **playwright.local.config.ts** - Test Configuration\nPlaywright config for local integration tests:\n\n**Key settings:**\n- `testDir: \"./e2e\"` — Test directory\n- `testMatch: \"local/**/*.spec.ts\"` — Test file pattern\n- `baseURL: \"http://localhost:3002\"` — Frontend URL\n- `workers: 1, fullyParallel: false` — Sequential test execution\n- `timeout: 60_000` — 60s per test\n- `viewport: 1280 × 1080` — Desktop Chrome\n\n**Dev server (Vite):**\n- Starts at `http://localhost:3002` on port 3002\n- Environment variables:\n  - `VITE_MOCK_MODE=false` — Use real wallet\n  - `VITE_TEST_WALLET=true` — Enable TestWalletProvider (reads `__TEST_WALLET_SEED__`)\n  - `VITE_RPC_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8899` — Local validator\n  - `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK=localnet` — Network mode\n\n---\n\n## Typical Test Pattern\n\n```typescript\nimport { test, expect } from \"./fixtures\";\nimport * as po from \"./helpers/page-objects\";\nimport * as onChain from \"./helpers/on-chain\";\nimport { fundTestWallets } from \"./helpers/wallets\";\n\ntest.beforeAll(async () => {\n  await fundTestWallets(); // Airdrop SOL\n});\n\ntest(\"full game flow\", async ({ playerAPage, playerBPage, playerAKeypair, playerBKeypair, connection }) => {\n  // Navigate both players to coinflip\n  await po.navigateToCoinflip(playerAPage);\n  await po.navigateToCoinflip(playerBPage);\n\n  // Player A creates a game\n  await po.createMatch(playerAPage, \"iron\", \"heads\");\n\n  // Verify on-chain state\n  const { matchPda } = await onChain.assertMatchCreated(\n    connection,\n    playerAKeypair.publicKey,\n    0, // tier 0 = iron\n    0, // side 0 = heads\n  );\n\n  // Player B joins\n  await po.joinMatch(playerBPage);\n\n  // Wait for game to resolve\n  const resultA = await po.waitForResult(playerAPage);\n  const resultB = await po.waitForResult(playerBPage);\n\n  // Claim payouts\n  await po.claimOrSettle(playerAPage);\n  await po.claimOrSettle(playerBPage);\n\n  // Verify on-chain: match closed, treasury received fee, profiles updated\n  await onChain.assertMatchClosed(connection, matchPda);\n  // ... assert treasury fee, player profiles\n});\n```\n\nAll files are comprehensive and ready to use for writing integration tests!"}],"totalDurationMs":23513,"totalTokens":41739,"totalToolUseCount":5,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14918,"cache_read_input_tokens":24645,"output_tokens":2169,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_