{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BFyKfoXi69m5yijZjFc8qv","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have the complete content of the coinflip bankrun test file. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary of how coinflip matches are resolved programmatically:\n\n---\n\n## Coinflip Match Resolution Flow\n\n### Key Resolution Instruction: `claim_payout`\n\nThe resolution happens through the **`claim_payout`** instruction (lines 274-295), which is **permissionless** — either the creator or opponent can trigger it:\n\n```typescript\nasync function claimPayout(\n  t: TestContext,\n  callerProgram: Program<Coinflip>,\n  callerPubkey: PublicKey\n) {\n  await callerProgram.methods\n    .claimPayout()\n    .accounts({\n      caller: callerPubkey,\n      coinflipMatch: t.matchPda,\n      config: t.configPda,\n      treasury: t.treasury.publicKey,\n      creator: t.creator,\n      opponent: t.opponent.publicKey,\n      randomnessAccount: t.mockRandomness.publicKey,\n      creatorProfile: t.creatorProfilePda,\n      opponentProfile: t.opponentProfilePda,\n      platformProgram: PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID,\n      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n    })\n    .rpc();\n}\n```\n\n**Key Points:**\n- **Caller** can be either player (test line 622-623 proves this)\n- **Payout goes to the derived winner**, not necessarily the caller\n- The instruction doesn't require the caller to be the match creator or opponent — it only needs to be authorized to trigger settlement\n\n---\n\n### Required Accounts for Resolution\n\n1. **`coinflipMatch`** (PDA) — The match account to settle\n   - Seeds: `[\"match\", creator.pubkey]`\n   - Derives uniquely per creator (lines 60-66)\n\n2. **`randomnessAccount`** — The VRF fulfillment oracle\n   - Mock in tests: `mockRandomness` (32-byte buffer)\n   - Byte `[0]` determines outcome: `2 % 2 = 0 (HEADS)` vs `1 % 2 = 1 (TAILS)`\n   - Must be **fulfilled** (non-zero first byte) or claim fails (line 648-663)\n\n3. **`treasury`** — Fee recipient\n   - Receives exact 3% fee (300 bps) from the pool (lines 564-566, 737-738)\n\n4. **Player Profiles** (via CPI to platform program)\n   - `creatorProfile` PDA\n   - `opponentProfile` PDA\n   - Updated with game stats: wins, total games, total wagered, total won (lines 726-755)\n\n5. **Config PDAs**\n   - `config` — Coinflip config (contains authority, treasury)\n   - `platformProgram` ID — For CPI to update profiles\n\n---\n\n### Program IDs & Constants\n\n```typescript\n// Lines 21-29: Loaded from IDL files at runtime\nconst PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(IDL.address);           // Coinflip program\nconst PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(PLATFORM_IDL.address);  // Platform program\n\n// Lines 34-39: Game constants\nconst SIDE_HEADS = 0;\nconst SIDE_TAILS = 1;\nconst TIER_IRON = 0;\nconst TIER_IRON_AMOUNT = 5_000_000;  // 0.005 SOL in lamports\nconst TOTAL_FEE_BPS = 300;           // 3% total fee\nconst DEFAULT_RESOLVE_TIMEOUT = 120; // seconds for timeout fallback\n```\n\n---\n\n### How Winner is Resolved\n\nThe VRF randomness is checked on-chain:\n\n```typescript\n// Lines 42-53: Mock randomness examples\nconst RANDOMNESS_HEADS = (() => {\n  const buf = Buffer.alloc(32);\n  buf[0] = 2;  // byte[0] % 2 = 0 → HEADS\n  return buf;\n})();\n\nconst RANDOMNESS_TAILS = (() => {\n  const buf = Buffer.alloc(32);\n  buf[0] = 1;  // byte[0] % 2 = 1 → TAILS\n  return buf;\n})();\n```\n\n**Resolution Logic:**\n- If creator chose HEADS and `randomness[0] % 2 == 0` → creator wins\n- If creator chose HEADS and `randomness[0] % 2 == 1` → opponent wins\n- Opposite applies if creator chose TAILS\n\n---\n\n### Payout Calculation\n\n```typescript\nconst pool = TIER_IRON_AMOUNT * 2;        // Both players' stakes\nconst fee = Math.floor((pool * TOTAL_FEE_BPS) / 10_000);  // 3%\nconst payout = pool - fee;\n// Winner receives: payout\n// Treasury receives: fee\n// Loser receives: nothing\n```\n\nExample (lines 564-566):\n- Pool: 10M lamports (5M + 5M)\n- Fee: 300K lamports (3%)\n- Winner payout: 9.7M lamports\n\n---\n\n### Match States & Transitions\n\n```typescript\n// Lines 379-393: Create → Waiting phase\n{ waiting: {} }  // Created by creator\n\n// Lines 461-484: Join → Locked phase\n{ locked: {} }   // Opponent joins, VRF request issued\n\n// After claim_payout: PDA closed\n// Account destroyed, rent refunded (tests line 643-645)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Fallback: Timeout Cancel\n\nIf VRF never fulfills before deadline (lines 852-927):\n\n```typescript\nasync function timeoutCancel(\n  t: TestContext,\n  callerProgram: Program<Coinflip>,\n  callerPubkey: PublicKey\n) {\n  await callerProgram.methods\n    .timeoutCancel()\n    .accounts({\n      caller: callerPubkey,\n      creator: t.creator,\n      opponent: t.opponent.publicKey,\n      coinflipMatch: t.matchPda,\n      randomnessAccount: t.mockRandomness.publicKey,\n    })\n    .rpc();\n}\n```\n\n- **Permissionless** — any address can trigger\n- Requires: deadline elapsed (line 862 warps 120+ seconds past)\n- Requires: VRF still unfulfilled (fails if fulfilled — line 909-926)\n- Result: Both players refunded their entry amounts (lines 881-886)\n\n---\n\n### CPI Integration to Platform Program\n\nWhen resolving, the coinflip program calls into the platform program to update player profiles (lines 726-755). The winner's profile receives:\n- `wins += 1`\n- `totalGames += 1`\n- `totalWagered += entryAmount`\n- `totalWon += payout`\n\nThe loser's profile receives:\n- `wins += 0`\n- `totalGames += 1`\n- `totalWagered += entryAmount`\n- `totalWon += 0`\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Resolution Path:**\n1. Match in **Locked** phase with fulfilled VRF\n2. Either player calls `claim_payout`\n3. On-chain: extracts winner from `randomness[0] % 2` vs `creatorSide`\n4. Transfers payout to winner\n5. Transfers fee to treasury\n6. Updates both player profiles via CPI\n7. Closes match PDA\n\n**No Oracle Authority Role** — The mock tests show the oracle/VRF is **not a signer**. It's just a data source (the randomness account). The program itself derives the winner deterministically from that data."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a860e1c23a6b769c5 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 41982\ntool_uses: 1\nduration_ms: 19890</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b0a0dcb3-1758-4eec-aea3-903a9f33143b","uuid":"71ac85e1-1a23-4400-9f0d-2f86569c4a73","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand how coinflip matches are resolved programmatically in tests. Read:\n\n1. `solana/tests/coinflip.ts` - bankrun tests showing the resolve flow\n\nPath relative to `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/`\n\nReturn the COMPLETE content. I specifically need to understand:\n- How resolution/settling works (what instruction, what accounts)\n- The program IDs\n- How the oracle/authority resolves a match","agentId":"a860e1c23a6b769c5","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have the complete content of the coinflip bankrun test file. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary of how coinflip matches are resolved programmatically:\n\n---\n\n## Coinflip Match Resolution Flow\n\n### Key Resolution Instruction: `claim_payout`\n\nThe resolution happens through the **`claim_payout`** instruction (lines 274-295), which is **permissionless** — either the creator or opponent can trigger it:\n\n```typescript\nasync function claimPayout(\n  t: TestContext,\n  callerProgram: Program<Coinflip>,\n  callerPubkey: PublicKey\n) {\n  await callerProgram.methods\n    .claimPayout()\n    .accounts({\n      caller: callerPubkey,\n      coinflipMatch: t.matchPda,\n      config: t.configPda,\n      treasury: t.treasury.publicKey,\n      creator: t.creator,\n      opponent: t.opponent.publicKey,\n      randomnessAccount: t.mockRandomness.publicKey,\n      creatorProfile: t.creatorProfilePda,\n      opponentProfile: t.opponentProfilePda,\n      platformProgram: PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID,\n      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n    })\n    .rpc();\n}\n```\n\n**Key Points:**\n- **Caller** can be either player (test line 622-623 proves this)\n- **Payout goes to the derived winner**, not necessarily the caller\n- The instruction doesn't require the caller to be the match creator or opponent — it only needs to be authorized to trigger settlement\n\n---\n\n### Required Accounts for Resolution\n\n1. **`coinflipMatch`** (PDA) — The match account to settle\n   - Seeds: `[\"match\", creator.pubkey]`\n   - Derives uniquely per creator (lines 60-66)\n\n2. **`randomnessAccount`** — The VRF fulfillment oracle\n   - Mock in tests: `mockRandomness` (32-byte buffer)\n   - Byte `[0]` determines outcome: `2 % 2 = 0 (HEADS)` vs `1 % 2 = 1 (TAILS)`\n   - Must be **fulfilled** (non-zero first byte) or claim fails (line 648-663)\n\n3. **`treasury`** — Fee recipient\n   - Receives exact 3% fee (300 bps) from the pool (lines 564-566, 737-738)\n\n4. **Player Profiles** (via CPI to platform program)\n   - `creatorProfile` PDA\n   - `opponentProfile` PDA\n   - Updated with game stats: wins, total games, total wagered, total won (lines 726-755)\n\n5. **Config PDAs**\n   - `config` — Coinflip config (contains authority, treasury)\n   - `platformProgram` ID — For CPI to update profiles\n\n---\n\n### Program IDs & Constants\n\n```typescript\n// Lines 21-29: Loaded from IDL files at runtime\nconst PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(IDL.address);           // Coinflip program\nconst PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(PLATFORM_IDL.address);  // Platform program\n\n// Lines 34-39: Game constants\nconst SIDE_HEADS = 0;\nconst SIDE_TAILS = 1;\nconst TIER_IRON = 0;\nconst TIER_IRON_AMOUNT = 5_000_000;  // 0.005 SOL in lamports\nconst TOTAL_FEE_BPS = 300;           // 3% total fee\nconst DEFAULT_RESOLVE_TIMEOUT = 120; // seconds for timeout fallback\n```\n\n---\n\n### How Winner is Resolved\n\nThe VRF randomness is checked on-chain:\n\n```typescript\n// Lines 42-53: Mock randomness examples\nconst RANDOMNESS_HEADS = (() => {\n  const buf = Buffer.alloc(32);\n  buf[0] = 2;  // byte[0] % 2 = 0 → HEADS\n  return buf;\n})();\n\nconst RANDOMNESS_TAILS = (() => {\n  const buf = Buffer.alloc(32);\n  buf[0] = 1;  // byte[0] % 2 = 1 → TAILS\n  return buf;\n})();\n```\n\n**Resolution Logic:**\n- If creator chose HEADS and `randomness[0] % 2 == 0` → creator wins\n- If creator chose HEADS and `randomness[0] % 2 == 1` → opponent wins\n- Opposite applies if creator chose TAILS\n\n---\n\n### Payout Calculation\n\n```typescript\nconst pool = TIER_IRON_AMOUNT * 2;        // Both players' stakes\nconst fee = Math.floor((pool * TOTAL_FEE_BPS) / 10_000);  // 3%\nconst payout = pool - fee;\n// Winner receives: payout\n// Treasury receives: fee\n// Loser receives: nothing\n```\n\nExample (lines 564-566):\n- Pool: 10M lamports (5M + 5M)\n- Fee: 300K lamports (3%)\n- Winner payout: 9.7M lamports\n\n---\n\n### Match States & Transitions\n\n```typescript\n// Lines 379-393: Create → Waiting phase\n{ waiting: {} }  // Created by creator\n\n// Lines 461-484: Join → Locked phase\n{ locked: {} }   // Opponent joins, VRF request issued\n\n// After claim_payout: PDA closed\n// Account destroyed, rent refunded (tests line 643-645)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Fallback: Timeout Cancel\n\nIf VRF never fulfills before deadline (lines 852-927):\n\n```typescript\nasync function timeoutCancel(\n  t: TestContext,\n  callerProgram: Program<Coinflip>,\n  callerPubkey: PublicKey\n) {\n  await callerProgram.methods\n    .timeoutCancel()\n    .accounts({\n      caller: callerPubkey,\n      creator: t.creator,\n      opponent: t.opponent.publicKey,\n      coinflipMatch: t.matchPda,\n      randomnessAccount: t.mockRandomness.publicKey,\n    })\n    .rpc();\n}\n```\n\n- **Permissionless** — any address can trigger\n- Requires: deadline elapsed (line 862 warps 120+ seconds past)\n- Requires: VRF still unfulfilled (fails if fulfilled — line 909-926)\n- Result: Both players refunded their entry amounts (lines 881-886)\n\n---\n\n### CPI Integration to Platform Program\n\nWhen resolving, the coinflip program calls into the platform program to update player profiles (lines 726-755). The winner's profile receives:\n- `wins += 1`\n- `totalGames += 1`\n- `totalWagered += entryAmount`\n- `totalWon += payout`\n\nThe loser's profile receives:\n- `wins += 0`\n- `totalGames += 1`\n- `totalWagered += entryAmount`\n- `totalWon += 0`\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Resolution Path:**\n1. Match in **Locked** phase with fulfilled VRF\n2. Either player calls `claim_payout`\n3. On-chain: extracts winner from `randomness[0] % 2` vs `creatorSide`\n4. Transfers payout to winner\n5. Transfers fee to treasury\n6. Updates both player profiles via CPI\n7. Closes match PDA\n\n**No Oracle Authority Role** — The mock tests show the oracle/VRF is **not a signer**. It's just a data source (the randomness account). The program itself derives the winner deterministically from that data."}],"totalDurationMs":19890,"totalTokens":41982,"totalToolUseCount":1,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":15517,"cache_read_input_tokens":24573,"output_tokens":1887,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":15517,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
