{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Vx9tFtGSmGVy6n1zwCoNRL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * On-chain assertion helpers for local E2E tests.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Provides RPC-based helpers to query and assert match PDA state,\n     5→ * treasury fee deltas, and player profile stat updates.\n     6→ */\n     7→import { Connection, PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n     8→import { Program, AnchorProvider, type Idl } from \"@coral-xyz/anchor\";\n     9→import {\n    10→  CoinflipIDL,\n    11→  PlatformIDL,\n    12→  type Coinflip,\n    13→  type Platform,\n    14→} from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n    15→\n    16→// ============ Program IDs ============\n    17→\n    18→/** Coinflip program address (from IDL). */\n    19→export const COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(CoinflipIDL.address);\n    20→\n    21→/** Platform program address (from IDL). */\n    22→export const PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(PlatformIDL.address);\n    23→\n    24→/** Platform fee: 300 basis points = 3%. */\n    25→export const FEE_BPS = 300;\n    26→\n    27→// ============ PDA Derivation ============\n    28→\n    29→/** Derive the match PDA for a creator. Seeds: [\"match\", creator]. */\n    30→export function getMatchPda(creator: PublicKey): [PublicKey, number] {\n    31→  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    32→    [Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer()],\n    33→    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n    34→  );\n    35→}\n    36→\n    37→/** Derive the coinflip config PDA. Seeds: [\"coinflip_config\"]. */\n    38→export function getConfigPda(): [PublicKey, number] {\n    39→  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    40→    [Buffer.from(\"coinflip_config\")],\n    41→    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n    42→  );\n    43→}\n    44→\n    45→/** Derive a player profile PDA. Seeds: [\"player_profile\", wallet]. */\n    46→export function getPlayerProfilePda(wallet: PublicKey): [PublicKey, number] {\n    47→  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    48→    [Buffer.from(\"player_profile\"), wallet.toBuffer()],\n    49→    PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID,\n    50→  );\n    51→}\n    52→\n    53→// ============ Program Instances ============\n    54→\n    55→/**\n    56→ * Create a read-only Coinflip program instance.\n    57→ *\n    58→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n    59→ */\n    60→export function getCoinflipProgram(connection: Connection): Program<Coinflip> {\n    61→  const provider = new AnchorProvider(\n    62→    connection,\n    63→    {} as AnchorProvider[\"wallet\"],\n    64→    { commitment: \"confirmed\" },\n    65→  );\n    66→  return new Program(CoinflipIDL as Idl as Coinflip, provider);\n    67→}\n    68→\n    69→/**\n    70→ * Create a read-only Platform program instance.\n    71→ *\n    72→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n    73→ */\n    74→export function getPlatformProgram(connection: Connection): Program<Platform> {\n    75→  const provider = new AnchorProvider(\n    76→    connection,\n    77→    {} as AnchorProvider[\"wallet\"],\n    78→    { commitment: \"confirmed\" },\n    79→  );\n    80→  return new Program(PlatformIDL as Idl as Platform, provider);\n    81→}\n    82→\n    83→// ============ Account Types ============\n    84→\n    85→/** Deserialized match account shape. */\n    86→export interface MatchAccount {\n    87→  creator: PublicKey;\n    88→  opponent: PublicKey;\n    89→  tier: number;\n    90→  entryAmount: { toNumber(): number };\n    91→  creatorSide: number;\n    92→  phase: Record<string, object>;\n    93→  result: number;\n    94→  winner: PublicKey;\n    95→  claimed: boolean;\n    96→  createdAt: { toNumber(): number };\n    97→  lockedAt: { toNumber(): number };\n    98→  resolveDeadline: { toNumber(): number };\n    99→  vrfRequestKey: PublicKey;\n   100→  bump: number;\n   101→}\n   102→\n   103→/** Deserialized player profile account shape. */\n   104→export interface PlayerProfileAccount {\n   105→  authority: PublicKey;\n   106→  totalGames: { toNumber(): number };\n   107→  wins: { toNumber(): number };\n   108→  totalWagered: { toNumber(): number };\n   109→  totalWon: { toNumber(): number };\n   110→  bump: number;\n   111→}\n   112→\n   113→// ============ Fetch Helpers ============\n   114→\n   115→/**\n   116→ * Fetch a match PDA account. Returns null if the account is closed.\n   117→ *\n   118→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   119→ * @param matchPda - The match PDA address\n   120→ */\n   121→export async function fetchMatch(\n   122→  connection: Connection,\n   123→  matchPda: PublicKey,\n   124→): Promise<MatchAccount | null> {\n   125→  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n   126→  try {\n   127→    return (await program.account.coinflipMatch.fetch(\n   128→      matchPda,\n   129→    )) as unknown as MatchAccount;\n   130→  } catch {\n   131→    // Account not found (closed or never created)\n   132→    return null;\n   133→  }\n   134→}\n   135→\n   136→/**\n   137→ * Fetch a player profile PDA account. Returns null if it doesn't exist.\n   138→ *\n   139→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   140→ * @param profilePda - The player profile PDA address\n   141→ */\n   142→export async function fetchPlayerProfile(\n   143→  connection: Connection,\n   144→  profilePda: PublicKey,\n   145→): Promise<PlayerProfileAccount | null> {\n   146→  const program = getPlatformProgram(connection);\n   147→  try {\n   148→    return (await program.account.playerProfile.fetch(\n   149→      profilePda,\n   150→    )) as unknown as PlayerProfileAccount;\n   151→  } catch {\n   152→    return null;\n   153→  }\n   154→}\n   155→\n   156→/**\n   157→ * Get the treasury wallet address from the coinflip config PDA.\n   158→ *\n   159→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   160→ */\n   161→export async function getTreasuryAddress(\n   162→  connection: Connection,\n   163→): Promise<PublicKey> {\n   164→  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n   165→  const [configPda] = getConfigPda();\n   166→  const config = await program.account.coinflipConfig.fetch(configPda);\n   167→  return (config as unknown as { treasury: PublicKey }).treasury;\n   168→}\n   169→\n   170→// ============ Balance Helpers ============\n   171→\n   172→/**\n   173→ * Get the SOL balance of an address in lamports.\n   174→ *\n   175→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   176→ * @param address - Public key to check\n   177→ */\n   178→export async function getBalanceLamports(\n   179→  connection: Connection,\n   180→  address: PublicKey,\n   181→): Promise<number> {\n   182→  return connection.getBalance(address);\n   183→}\n   184→\n   185→/**\n   186→ * Capture a balance snapshot for later delta comparison.\n   187→ *\n   188→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   189→ * @param address - Public key to snapshot\n   190→ */\n   191→export async function snapshotBalance(\n   192→  connection: Connection,\n   193→  address: PublicKey,\n   194→): Promise<number> {\n   195→  return connection.getBalance(address);\n   196→}\n   197→\n   198→// ============ Fee Calculation ============\n   199→\n   200→/**\n   201→ * Calculate the expected fee and net payout for a coinflip match.\n   202→ * Mirrors on-chain logic: fee = floor(pool * FEE_BPS / 10_000).\n   203→ *\n   204→ * @param entryAmount - Single player's entry in lamports\n   205→ * @returns Object with pool, fee, and payout amounts in lamports\n   206→ */\n   207→export function calculateExpectedFee(entryAmount: number): {\n   208→  pool: number;\n   209→  fee: number;\n   210→  payout: number;\n   211→} {\n   212→  const pool = entryAmount * 2;\n   213→  const fee = Math.floor((pool * FEE_BPS) / 10_000);\n   214→  const payout = pool - fee;\n   215→  return { pool, fee, payout };\n   216→}\n   217→\n   218→// ============ Assertion Helpers ============\n   219→\n   220→/**\n   221→ * Assert match PDA state after creation (Waiting phase).\n   222→ *\n   223→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   224→ * @param creator - Creator's public key\n   225→ * @param expectedTier - Expected tier index\n   226→ * @param expectedSide - Expected creator side (0 = heads, 1 = tails)\n   227→ */\n   228→export async function assertMatchCreated(\n   229→  connection: Connection,\n   230→  creator: PublicKey,\n   231→  expectedTier: number,\n   232→  expectedSide: number,\n   233→): Promise<{ matchPda: PublicKey; match: MatchAccount }> {\n   234→  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(creator);\n   235→  const match = await fetchMatch(connection, matchPda);\n   236→  if (!match) throw new Error(`Match PDA not found for creator ${creator}`);\n   237→\n   238→  const phase = Object.keys(match.phase)[0];\n   239→  if (phase !== \"waiting\") {\n   240→    throw new Error(`Expected phase 'waiting', got '${phase}'`);\n   241→  }\n   242→  if (match.creator.toBase58() !== creator.toBase58()) {\n   243→    throw new Error(\"Match creator does not match expected creator\");\n   244→  }\n   245→  if (match.tier !== expectedTier) {\n   246→    throw new Error(`Expected tier ${expectedTier}, got ${match.tier}`);\n   247→  }\n   248→  if (match.creatorSide !== expectedSide) {\n   249→    throw new Error(`Expected side ${expectedSide}, got ${match.creatorSide}`);\n   250→  }\n   251→  if (match.opponent.toBase58() !== PublicKey.default.toBase58()) {\n   252→    throw new Error(\"Expected no opponent in waiting phase\");\n   253→  }\n   254→  if (match.claimed) {\n   255→    throw new Error(\"Expected claimed=false after creation\");\n   256→  }\n   257→\n   258→  return { matchPda, match };\n   259→}\n   260→\n   261→/**\n   262→ * Assert match PDA is closed (account no longer exists).\n   263→ *\n   264→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   265→ * @param matchPda - The match PDA address to check\n   266→ */\n   267→export async function assertMatchClosed(\n   268→  connection: Connection,\n   269→  matchPda: PublicKey,\n   270→): Promise<void> {\n   271→  const match = await fetchMatch(connection, matchPda);\n   272→  if (match !== null) {\n   273→    const phase = Object.keys(match.phase)[0];\n   274→    throw new Error(\n   275→      `Expected match PDA to be closed, but it still exists (phase: ${phase})`,\n   276→    );\n   277→  }\n   278→}\n   279→\n   280→/**\n   281→ * Assert that the treasury received the expected fee.\n   282→ * Call snapshotBalance before the payout, then call this after.\n   283→ *\n   284→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   285→ * @param treasury - Treasury public key\n   286→ * @param balanceBefore - Treasury balance in lamports before claim\n   287→ * @param entryAmount - Single player's entry in lamports\n   288→ */\n   289→export async function assertTreasuryFee(\n   290→  connection: Connection,\n   291→  treasury: PublicKey,\n   292→  balanceBefore: number,\n   293→  entryAmount: number,\n   294→): Promise<void> {\n   295→  const balanceAfter = await getBalanceLamports(connection, treasury);\n   296→  const { fee } = calculateExpectedFee(entryAmount);\n   297→  const actualDelta = balanceAfter - balanceBefore;\n   298→\n   299→  if (actualDelta !== fee) {\n   300→    throw new Error(\n   301→      `Treasury fee mismatch: expected ${fee} lamports, got delta ${actualDelta}`,\n   302→    );\n   303→  }\n   304→}\n   305→\n   306→/**\n   307→ * Assert player profile stats after a game.\n   308→ *\n   309→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   310→ * @param wallet - Player's wallet public key\n   311→ * @param expected - Expected stat values\n   312→ */\n   313→export async function assertPlayerProfile(\n   314→  connection: Connection,\n   315→  wallet: PublicKey,\n   316→  expected: {\n   317→    totalGames: number;\n   318→    wins: number;\n   319→    totalWagered: number;\n   320→    totalWon: number;\n   321→  },\n   322→): Promise<void> {\n   323→  const [profilePda] = getPlayerProfilePda(wallet);\n   324→  const profile = await fetchPlayerProfile(connection, profilePda);\n   325→  if (!profile) {\n   326→    throw new Error(`Player profile not found for ${wallet}`);\n   327→  }\n   328→\n   329→  const actual = {\n   330→    totalGames: profile.totalGames.toNumber(),\n   331→    wins: profile.wins.toNumber(),\n   332→    totalWagered: profile.totalWagered.toNumber(),\n   333→    totalWon: profile.totalWon.toNumber(),\n   334→  };\n   335→\n   336→  for (const key of Object.keys(expected) as (keyof typeof expected)[]) {\n   337→    if (actual[key] !== expected[key]) {\n   338→      throw new Error(\n   339→        `Profile ${key} mismatch for ${wallet}: expected ${expected[key]}, got ${actual[key]}`,\n   340→      );\n   341→    }\n   342→  }\n   343→}\n   344→\n   345→/**\n   346→ * Assert player profile stats changed by a specific delta since a snapshot.\n   347→ *\n   348→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   349→ * @param wallet - Player's wallet public key\n   350→ * @param before - Profile stats snapshot before the action\n   351→ * @param delta - Expected stat deltas\n   352→ */\n   353→export async function assertPlayerProfileDelta(\n   354→  connection: Connection,\n   355→  wallet: PublicKey,\n   356→  before: { totalGames: number; wins: number; totalWagered: number; totalWon: number },\n   357→  delta: { totalGames: number; wins: number; totalWagered: number; totalWon: number },\n   358→): Promise<void> {\n   359→  const expected = {\n   360→    totalGames: before.totalGames + delta.totalGames,\n   361→    wins: before.wins + delta.wins,\n   362→    totalWagered: before.totalWagered + delta.totalWagered,\n   363→    totalWon: before.totalWon + delta.totalWon,\n   364→  };\n   365→  await assertPlayerProfile(connection, wallet, expected);\n   366→}\n   367→\n   368→/**\n   369→ * Snapshot a player profile's current stats (for later delta comparison).\n   370→ * Returns zero-stats if the profile doesn't exist yet.\n   371→ *\n   372→ * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n   373→ * @param wallet - Player's wallet public key\n   374→ */\n   375→export async function snapshotPlayerProfile(\n   376→  connection: Connection,\n   377→  wallet: PublicKey,\n   378→): Promise<{ totalGames: number; wins: number; totalWagered: number; totalWon: number }> {\n   379→  const [profilePda] = getPlayerProfilePda(wallet);\n   380→  const profile = await fetchPlayerProfile(connection, profilePda);\n   381→  if (!profile) {\n   382→    return { totalGames: 0, wins: 0, totalWagered: 0, totalWon: 0 };\n   383→  }\n   384→  return {\n   385→    totalGames: profile.totalGames.toNumber(),\n   386→    wins: profile.wins.toNumber(),\n   387→    totalWagered: profile.totalWagered.toNumber(),\n   388→    totalWon: profile.totalWon.toNumber(),\n   389→  };\n   390→}\n   391→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b0a0dcb3-1758-4eec-aea3-903a9f33143b","uuid":"fd00ddf5-3504-4fbe-9f10-43145b69a529","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/on-chain.ts","content":"/**\n * On-chain assertion helpers for local E2E tests.\n *\n * Provides RPC-based helpers to query and assert match PDA state,\n * treasury fee deltas, and player profile stat updates.\n */\nimport { Connection, PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { Program, AnchorProvider, type Idl } from \"@coral-xyz/anchor\";\nimport {\n  CoinflipIDL,\n  PlatformIDL,\n  type Coinflip,\n  type Platform,\n} from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n\n// ============ Program IDs ============\n\n/** Coinflip program address (from IDL). */\nexport const COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(CoinflipIDL.address);\n\n/** Platform program address (from IDL). */\nexport const PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(PlatformIDL.address);\n\n/** Platform fee: 300 basis points = 3%. */\nexport const FEE_BPS = 300;\n\n// ============ PDA Derivation ============\n\n/** Derive the match PDA for a creator. Seeds: [\"match\", creator]. */\nexport function getMatchPda(creator: PublicKey): [PublicKey, number] {\n  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer()],\n    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n  );\n}\n\n/** Derive the coinflip config PDA. Seeds: [\"coinflip_config\"]. */\nexport function getConfigPda(): [PublicKey, number] {\n  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"coinflip_config\")],\n    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n  );\n}\n\n/** Derive a player profile PDA. Seeds: [\"player_profile\", wallet]. */\nexport function getPlayerProfilePda(wallet: PublicKey): [PublicKey, number] {\n  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"player_profile\"), wallet.toBuffer()],\n    PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID,\n  );\n}\n\n// ============ Program Instances ============\n\n/**\n * Create a read-only Coinflip program instance.\n *\n * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n */\nexport function getCoinflipProgram(connection: Connection): Program<Coinflip> {\n  const provider = new AnchorProvider(\n    connection,\n    {} as AnchorProvider[\"wallet\"],\n    { commitment: \"confirmed\" },\n  );\n  return new Program(CoinflipIDL as Idl as Coinflip, provider);\n}\n\n/**\n * Create a read-only Platform program instance.\n *\n * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n */\nexport function getPlatformProgram(connection: Connection): Program<Platform> {\n  const provider = new AnchorProvider(\n    connection,\n    {} as AnchorProvider[\"wallet\"],\n    { commitment: \"confirmed\" },\n  );\n  return new Program(PlatformIDL as Idl as Platform, provider);\n}\n\n// ============ Account Types ============\n\n/** Deserialized match account shape. */\nexport interface MatchAccount {\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  opponent: PublicKey;\n  tier: number;\n  entryAmount: { toNumber(): number };\n  creatorSide: number;\n  phase: Record<string, object>;\n  result: number;\n  winner: PublicKey;\n  claimed: boolean;\n  createdAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  lockedAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  resolveDeadline: { toNumber(): number };\n  vrfRequestKey: PublicKey;\n  bump: number;\n}\n\n/** Deserialized player profile account shape. */\nexport interface PlayerProfileAccount {\n  authority: PublicKey;\n  totalGames: { toNumber(): number };\n  wins: { toNumber(): number };\n  totalWagered: { toNumber(): number };\n  totalWon: { toNumber(): number };\n  bump: number;\n}\n\n// ============ Fetch Helpers ============\n\n/**\n * Fetch a match PDA account. Returns null if the account is closed.\n *\n * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n * @param matchPda - The match PDA address\n */\nexport async function fetchMatch(\n  connection: Connection,\n  matchPda: PublicKey,\n): Promise<MatchAccount | null> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n  try {\n    return (await program.account.coinflipMatch.fetch(\n      matchPda,\n    )) as unknown as MatchAccount;\n  } catch {\n    // Account not found (closed or never created)\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Fetch a player profile PDA account. Returns null if it doesn't exist.\n *\n * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n * @param profilePda - The player profile PDA address\n */\nexport async function fetchPlayerProfile(\n  connection: Connection,\n  profilePda: PublicKey,\n): Promise<PlayerProfileAccount | null> {\n  const program = getPlatformProgram(connection);\n  try {\n    return (await program.account.playerProfile.fetch(\n      profilePda,\n    )) as unknown as PlayerProfileAccount;\n  } catch {\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Get the treasury wallet address from the coinflip config PDA.\n *\n * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n */\nexport async function getTreasuryAddress(\n  connection: Connection,\n): Promise<PublicKey> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n  const [configPda] = getConfigPda();\n  const config = await program.account.coinflipConfig.fetch(configPda);\n  return (config as unknown as { treasury: PublicKey }).treasury;\n}\n\n// ============ Balance Helpers ============\n\n/**\n * Get the SOL balance of an address in lamports.\n *\n * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n * @param address - Public key to check\n */\nexport async function getBalanceLamports(\n  connection: Connection,\n  address: PublicKey,\n): Promise<number> {\n  return connection.getBalance(address);\n}\n\n/**\n * Capture a balance snapshot for later delta comparison.\n *\n * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n * @param address - Public key to snapshot\n */\nexport async function snapshotBalance(\n  connection: Connection,\n  address: PublicKey,\n): Promise<number> {\n  return connection.getBalance(address);\n}\n\n// ============ Fee Calculation ============\n\n/**\n * Calculate the expected fee and net payout for a coinflip match.\n * Mirrors on-chain logic: fee = floor(pool * FEE_BPS / 10_000).\n *\n * @param entryAmount - Single player's entry in lamports\n * @returns Object with pool, fee, and payout amounts in lamports\n */\nexport function calculateExpectedFee(entryAmount: number): {\n  pool: number;\n  fee: number;\n  payout: number;\n} {\n  const pool = entryAmount * 2;\n  const fee = Math.floor((pool * FEE_BPS) / 10_000);\n  const payout = pool - fee;\n  return { pool, fee, payout };\n}\n\n// ============ Assertion Helpers ============\n\n/**\n * Assert match PDA state after creation (Waiting phase).\n *\n * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n * @param creator - Creator's public key\n * @param expectedTier - Expected tier index\n * @param expectedSide - Expected creator side (0 = heads, 1 = tails)\n */\nexport async function assertMatchCreated(\n  connection: Connection,\n  creator: PublicKey,\n  expectedTier: number,\n  expectedSide: number,\n): Promise<{ matchPda: PublicKey; match: MatchAccount }> {\n  const [matchPda] = getMatchPda(creator);\n  const match = await fetchMatch(connection, matchPda);\n  if (!match) throw new Error(`Match PDA not found for creator ${creator}`);\n\n  const phase = Object.keys(match.phase)[0];\n  if (phase !== \"waiting\") {\n    throw new Error(`Expected phase 'waiting', got '${phase}'`);\n  }\n  if (match.creator.toBase58() !== creator.toBase58()) {\n    throw new Error(\"Match creator does not match expected creator\");\n  }\n  if (match.tier !== expectedTier) {\n    throw new Error(`Expected tier ${expectedTier}, got ${match.tier}`);\n  }\n  if (match.creatorSide !== expectedSide) {\n    throw new Error(`Expected side ${expectedSide}, got ${match.creatorSide}`);\n  }\n  if (match.opponent.toBase58() !== PublicKey.default.toBase58()) {\n    throw new Error(\"Expected no opponent in waiting phase\");\n  }\n  if (match.claimed) {\n    throw new Error(\"Expected claimed=false after creation\");\n  }\n\n  return { matchPda, match };\n}\n\n/**\n * Assert match PDA is closed (account no longer exists).\n *\n * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n * @param matchPda - The match PDA address to check\n */\nexport async function assertMatchClosed(\n  connection: Connection,\n  matchPda: PublicKey,\n): Promise<void> {\n  const match = await fetchMatch(connection, matchPda);\n  if (match !== null) {\n    const phase = Object.keys(match.phase)[0];\n    throw new Error(\n      `Expected match PDA to be closed, but it still exists (phase: ${phase})`,\n    );\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Assert that the treasury received the expected fee.\n * Call snapshotBalance before the payout, then call this after.\n *\n * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n * @param treasury - Treasury public key\n * @param balanceBefore - Treasury balance in lamports before claim\n * @param entryAmount - Single player's entry in lamports\n */\nexport async function assertTreasuryFee(\n  connection: Connection,\n  treasury: PublicKey,\n  balanceBefore: number,\n  entryAmount: number,\n): Promise<void> {\n  const balanceAfter = await getBalanceLamports(connection, treasury);\n  const { fee } = calculateExpectedFee(entryAmount);\n  const actualDelta = balanceAfter - balanceBefore;\n\n  if (actualDelta !== fee) {\n    throw new Error(\n      `Treasury fee mismatch: expected ${fee} lamports, got delta ${actualDelta}`,\n    );\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Assert player profile stats after a game.\n *\n * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n * @param wallet - Player's wallet public key\n * @param expected - Expected stat values\n */\nexport async function assertPlayerProfile(\n  connection: Connection,\n  wallet: PublicKey,\n  expected: {\n    totalGames: number;\n    wins: number;\n    totalWagered: number;\n    totalWon: number;\n  },\n): Promise<void> {\n  const [profilePda] = getPlayerProfilePda(wallet);\n  const profile = await fetchPlayerProfile(connection, profilePda);\n  if (!profile) {\n    throw new Error(`Player profile not found for ${wallet}`);\n  }\n\n  const actual = {\n    totalGames: profile.totalGames.toNumber(),\n    wins: profile.wins.toNumber(),\n    totalWagered: profile.totalWagered.toNumber(),\n    totalWon: profile.totalWon.toNumber(),\n  };\n\n  for (const key of Object.keys(expected) as (keyof typeof expected)[]) {\n    if (actual[key] !== expected[key]) {\n      throw new Error(\n        `Profile ${key} mismatch for ${wallet}: expected ${expected[key]}, got ${actual[key]}`,\n      );\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Assert player profile stats changed by a specific delta since a snapshot.\n *\n * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n * @param wallet - Player's wallet public key\n * @param before - Profile stats snapshot before the action\n * @param delta - Expected stat deltas\n */\nexport async function assertPlayerProfileDelta(\n  connection: Connection,\n  wallet: PublicKey,\n  before: { totalGames: number; wins: number; totalWagered: number; totalWon: number },\n  delta: { totalGames: number; wins: number; totalWagered: number; totalWon: number },\n): Promise<void> {\n  const expected = {\n    totalGames: before.totalGames + delta.totalGames,\n    wins: before.wins + delta.wins,\n    totalWagered: before.totalWagered + delta.totalWagered,\n    totalWon: before.totalWon + delta.totalWon,\n  };\n  await assertPlayerProfile(connection, wallet, expected);\n}\n\n/**\n * Snapshot a player profile's current stats (for later delta comparison).\n * Returns zero-stats if the profile doesn't exist yet.\n *\n * @param connection - Solana RPC connection\n * @param wallet - Player's wallet public key\n */\nexport async function snapshotPlayerProfile(\n  connection: Connection,\n  wallet: PublicKey,\n): Promise<{ totalGames: number; wins: number; totalWagered: number; totalWon: number }> {\n  const [profilePda] = getPlayerProfilePda(wallet);\n  const profile = await fetchPlayerProfile(connection, profilePda);\n  if (!profile) {\n    return { totalGames: 0, wins: 0, totalWagered: 0, totalWon: 0 };\n  }\n  return {\n    totalGames: profile.totalGames.toNumber(),\n    wins: profile.wins.toNumber(),\n    totalWagered: profile.totalWagered.toNumber(),\n    totalWon: profile.totalWon.toNumber(),\n  };\n}\n","numLines":391,"startLine":1,"totalLines":391}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0119aQwectaYqZqzGGPTjXMG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding. The key challenge is: how do I programmatically resolve a match in the local E2E test?\n\nLooking at the bankrun tests, resolution works by:\n1. Match is in \"locked\" phase after join\n2. VRF randomness account has data written to it\n3. `claim_payout` instruction reads the randomness account and determines winner\n\nIn the local validator, the ORAO VRF program won't exist. So when `joinMatch` is called from the UI, it will try to CPI to the ORAO VRF program and fail.\n\nLet me re-read the chain.ts more carefully to understand how joinMatch works.\n\n\nActually, I need to look at the coinflip program source to understand what the join_match instruction does. The bootstrap script only loads the coinflip and platform programs, not the ORAO VRF program, which means joinMatch through the UI will fail when it tries to interact with the VRF program. I should check if there's a local or mock mode in chain.ts that handles this, though the environment config shows `VITE_MOCK_MODE=false` and `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK=local`, which suggests it's trying to use real wallet interactions.\n\nLooking at the chain.ts code and the agent summary, buildJoinMatchTx calls joinMatch and fetches the Orao treasury from a network state account. This means the join instruction needs to interact with the ORAO VRF program to request randomness and requires the ORAO treasury address—both of which need the VRF program deployed on the local validator. Since this is iteration 8 and the infrastructure items are supposedly complete, the VRF deployment issue must have already been addressed.\n\nBut looking at the spec more carefully, the test flow is: create match through UI, join match through UI (which triggers the VRF request), resolve programmatically via direct RPC, then claim through UI. The challenge is getting the ORAO VRF program available on the local validator—I could load the binary via `--bpf-program` if I have the .so file, create a mock VRF program, or skip the UI for the join step entirely.\n\nThe spec explicitly requires both create and join to go through the UI though, so I should focus on including the actual ORAO VRF program. Let me check if it's already in the project or if there's a known address I can use.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9833,"cache_read_input_tokens":57124,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9833},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b0a0dcb3-1758-4eec-aea3-903a9f33143b","uuid":"caf41aa3-65ff-4aac-9193-f144ec90921b"}
