{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LSyZ9Lz3n3Z9ZghgA4zcQo","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information needed. Let me compile the comprehensive report.\n\n## Summary: `join_match` Instruction Analysis\n\n### Full `join_match` Instruction Handler\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/join_match.rs`\n\n```rust\n/// Opponent joins a match, deposits SOL, and requests Orao VRF.\n#[derive(Accounts)]\npub struct JoinMatch<'info> {\n    /// The opponent joining the match. Must sign and fund their escrow.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub opponent: Signer<'info>,\n\n    /// The match PDA to join.\n    #[account(\n        mut,\n        seeds = [b\"match\", coinflip_match.creator.as_ref()],\n        bump = coinflip_match.bump,\n    )]\n    pub coinflip_match: Account<'info, CoinflipMatch>,\n\n    /// The config PDA.\n    #[account(\n        seeds = [b\"coinflip_config\"],\n        bump = config.bump,\n    )]\n    pub config: Account<'info, CoinflipConfig>,\n\n    /// Orao VRF program.\n    /// CHECK: Validated by Orao VRF CPI internally.\n    pub orao_program: UncheckedAccount<'info>,\n\n    /// Orao network state PDA.\n    /// CHECK: Validated by Orao VRF CPI internally.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub orao_network_state: UncheckedAccount<'info>,\n\n    /// Orao treasury for VRF fee payment.\n    /// CHECK: Validated by Orao VRF CPI internally.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub orao_treasury: UncheckedAccount<'info>,\n\n    /// Orao randomness account (created by Orao CPI).\n    /// CHECK: Orao VRF CPI validates and initializes this account.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub orao_random: UncheckedAccount<'info>,\n\n    pub system_program: Program<'info, System>,\n}\n\npub fn handler(ctx: Context<JoinMatch>) -> Result<()> {\n    let coinflip_match = &ctx.accounts.coinflip_match;\n\n    // Validate Waiting → Locked transition via shared lifecycle\n    lifecycle::transition(coinflip_match.phase, RoundPhase::Locked)?;\n\n    // Opponent cannot be the creator\n    require!(\n        ctx.accounts.opponent.key() != coinflip_match.creator,\n        CoinflipError::CannotJoinOwnMatch\n    );\n\n    let entry_amount = coinflip_match.entry_amount;\n    let opponent_key = ctx.accounts.opponent.key();\n\n    // Transfer entry_amount from opponent to match PDA (escrow) via shared helper\n    transfer_lamports_to_pda(\n        &ctx.accounts.opponent.to_account_info(),\n        &ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.to_account_info(),\n        entry_amount,\n        &ctx.accounts.system_program.to_account_info(),\n    )?;\n\n    // Request Orao VRF — use match PDA key as unique seed\n    let seed: [u8; 32] = ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.key().to_bytes();\n    vrf_orao::request_orao_randomness(\n        &ctx.accounts.orao_program.to_account_info(),\n        &ctx.accounts.orao_network_state.to_account_info(),\n        &ctx.accounts.orao_treasury.to_account_info(),\n        &ctx.accounts.orao_random.to_account_info(),\n        &ctx.accounts.opponent.to_account_info(),\n        &ctx.accounts.system_program.to_account_info(),\n        seed,\n    )?;\n\n    // Update match state\n    let now = Clock::get()?.unix_timestamp;\n    let coinflip_match = &mut ctx.accounts.coinflip_match;\n    coinflip_match.opponent = opponent_key;\n    coinflip_match.phase = RoundPhase::Locked;\n    coinflip_match.locked_at = now;\n    coinflip_match.resolve_deadline = now + DEFAULT_RESOLVE_TIMEOUT_SECONDS;\n    coinflip_match.vrf_request_key = ctx.accounts.orao_random.key();\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\n### Accounts Struct Breakdown\n\n| Account | Type | Mutable | Purpose |\n|---------|------|---------|---------|\n| `opponent` | Signer | Yes | The player joining; pays entry amount and signs the tx |\n| `coinflip_match` | PDA (seeds: `[\"match\", creator]`) | Yes | Match state; gets opponent deposited and phase updated |\n| `config` | PDA (seeds: `[\"coinflip_config\"]`) | No | Global config (unused in join_match logic, passed for consistency) |\n| `orao_program` | UncheckedAccount | No | Orao VRF program (CPI target) |\n| `orao_network_state` | UncheckedAccount | Yes | Orao's network state PDA (mutation during VRF CPI) |\n| `orao_treasury` | UncheckedAccount | Yes | Orao's treasury account (receives VRF fee) |\n| `orao_random` | UncheckedAccount | Yes | Orao's randomness account PDA (initialized by Orao CPI) |\n| `system_program` | Program | No | Solana System Program (escrow transfer + VRF CPI) |\n\n### VRF Request Details\n\n**VRF Seed**: The match PDA's public key is used as the seed for the VRF request:\n```rust\nlet seed: [u8; 32] = ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.key().to_bytes();\n```\n\n**VRF Call**: Delegates to shared module `vrf_orao::request_orao_randomness()` which is **feature-gated**:\n\n---\n\n### How Tests Handle VRF (Bankrun + Mock VRF)\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/coinflip.ts`\n\n#### 1. **Mock VRF Setup (Lines 41–55)**\n\nTests define mock randomness buffers instead of relying on real Orao VRF:\n\n```typescript\n// Mock VRF randomness buffers (32 bytes each)\n// HEADS: byte[0]=2 → 2%2=0=HEADS, non-zero so is_fulfilled=true\nconst RANDOMNESS_HEADS = (() => {\n  const buf = Buffer.alloc(32);\n  buf[0] = 2;\n  return buf;\n})();\n\n// TAILS: byte[0]=1 → 1%2=1=TAILS, non-zero so is_fulfilled=true\nconst RANDOMNESS_TAILS = (() => {\n  const buf = Buffer.alloc(32);\n  buf[0] = 1;\n  return buf;\n})();\n\n// Unfulfilled: all zeros → is_fulfilled=false\nconst RANDOMNESS_UNFULFILLED = Buffer.alloc(32);\n```\n\n#### 2. **Mock Orao Accounts Creation (Lines 124–149)**\n\nTest context sets up fake Orao accounts (all with default SystemProgram ownership):\n\n```typescript\nconst mockOraoProgram = Keypair.generate();\nconst mockOraoNetworkState = Keypair.generate();\nconst mockOraoTreasury = Keypair.generate();\nconst mockRandomness = Keypair.generate();\n\nconst context = await startAnchor(\"./\", [], [\n  { address: opponent.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData() },\n  { address: treasury.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData() },\n  // Mock Orao accounts (UncheckedAccount, CPI is no-op under mock-vrf)\n  { address: mockOraoProgram.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData() },\n  { address: mockOraoNetworkState.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData() },\n  { address: mockOraoTreasury.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData() },\n  // Mock randomness account — starts unfulfilled (32 zero bytes)\n  {\n    address: mockRandomness.publicKey,\n    info: {\n      lamports: LAMPORTS_PER_SOL,\n      data: RANDOMNESS_UNFULFILLED,\n      owner: SystemProgram.programId,\n      executable: false,\n    },\n  },\n]);\n```\n\n#### 3. **`joinMatch()` Helper (Lines 258–272)**\n\nTests call `joinMatch()` with the mock Orao accounts:\n\n```typescript\nasync function joinMatch(t: TestContext) {\n  await t.opponentProgram.methods\n    .joinMatch()\n    .accounts({\n      opponent: t.opponent.publicKey,\n      coinflipMatch: t.matchPda,\n      config: t.configPda,\n      oraoProgram: t.mockOraoProgram.publicKey,\n      oraoNetworkState: t.mockOraoNetworkState.publicKey,\n      oraoTreasury: t.mockOraoTreasury.publicKey,\n      oraoRandom: t.mockRandomness.publicKey,\n      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n    })\n    .rpc();\n}\n```\n\n#### 4. **Mock Randomness Setting (Lines 325–332)**\n\nAfter a join, tests manually inject fulfilled randomness into the mock randomness account:\n\n```typescript\nfunction setMockRandomness(t: TestContext, data: Buffer) {\n  t.context.setAccount(t.mockRandomness.publicKey, {\n    lamports: LAMPORTS_PER_SOL,\n    data,\n    owner: SystemProgram.programId,\n    executable: false,\n  });\n}\n\n// Usage in tests:\nsetMockRandomness(t, RANDOMNESS_HEADS);\nsetMockRandomness(t, RANDOMNESS_TAILS);\n```\n\n#### 5. **Feature Flag: `mock-vrf`**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/Cargo.toml`\n\n```toml\n[features]\nno-entrypoint = []\nno-idl = []\nno-log-ix-name = []\ncpi = [\"no-entrypoint\"]\ndefault = [\"mock-vrf\"]  # <-- Tests build with mock-vrf enabled\nmock-vrf = [\"rng-shared/mock-vrf\"]\n```\n\nThis enables the **mock VRF implementation** in the shared crate:\n\n---\n\n### VRF Module Feature-Gated Behavior\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/vrf_orao.rs`\n\n#### Real Mode (`#[cfg(not(feature = \"mock-vrf\"))]`)\n\n```rust\npub fn request_orao_randomness<'info>(\n    orao_program: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    network_state: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    treasury: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    random: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    payer: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    system_program: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    seed: [u8; 32],\n) -> Result<()> {\n    let cpi_accounts = orao_solana_vrf::cpi::accounts::RequestV2 {\n        payer: payer.clone(),\n        network_state: network_state.clone(),\n        treasury: treasury.clone(),\n        request: random.clone(),\n        system_program: system_program.clone(),\n    };\n    let cpi_ctx = CpiContext::new(orao_program.clone(), cpi_accounts);\n    orao_solana_vrf::cpi::request_v2(cpi_ctx, seed)\n}\n```\n\n- **Performs actual CPI** into the real Orao VRF program\n- **RequestV2 CPI**: Initializes the randomness account and deducts fee from payer (opponent)\n- Uses `orao-solana-vrf` crate (`v0.7.0`) with `\"cpi\"` feature\n\n#### Mock Mode (`#[cfg(feature = \"mock-vrf\")]`)\n\n```rust\npub fn request_orao_randomness<'info>(\n    _orao_program: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    _network_state: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    _treasury: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    _random: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    _payer: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    _system_program: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    _seed: [u8; 32],\n) -> Result<()> {\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\n- **No-op**: CPI is skipped entirely\n- Tests manually inject randomness into the account data (see `setMockRandomness` above)\n- No fee is deducted from payer\n\n#### Randomness Reading (Feature-Gated)\n\n**Real Mode**: Deserializes `orao_solana_vrf::state::RandomnessAccountData` and extracts fulfilled 64-byte randomness\n\n**Mock Mode**: Reads raw 32 bytes directly from account data; checks if any byte is non-zero (is_fulfilled)\n\n---\n\n## Key Findings\n\n1. **No Real Orao Integration in Tests**: Tests use **mock Orao accounts** (dummy keypairs with SystemProgram ownership).\n\n2. **Feature-Gated VRF**: The `mock-vrf` feature flag (enabled by default in Cargo.toml) switches the entire VRF module to no-op CPI and raw byte reading.\n\n3. **VRF Request Seed**: Uses the match PDA public key directly as the 32-byte seed for the Orao VRF request.\n\n4. **Randomness Encoding**: Tests encode coinflip results in the first byte:\n   - `byte[0] % 2 == 0` → HEADS\n   - `byte[0] % 2 == 1` → TAILS\n\n5. **VRF Audit Trail**: The `vrf_request_key` field in `CoinflipMatch` stores the randomness account address for later verification at claim time.\n\n6. **Timeout Fallback**: If VRF doesn't fulfill within `DEFAULT_RESOLVE_TIMEOUT_SECONDS`, either player can refund via `timeout_cancel`."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a43965a69e0c5d654 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 52104\ntool_uses: 15\nduration_ms: 44388</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b0a0dcb3-1758-4eec-aea3-903a9f33143b","uuid":"4a6d89a9-1f76-4f6a-bf46-f083eb9082ad","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the `join_match` instruction in the coinflip Solana program. Look at:\n\n1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/` - find the join_match instruction handler and its accounts struct\n2. Check what accounts are needed, specifically related to ORAO VRF (randomness request, VRF program, VRF treasury, etc.)\n3. Check if there's any mock VRF program or test VRF setup in the project\n\nAlso look at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/coinflip.ts` to see how the bankrun tests handle the VRF program during join. Do they mock it? Do they use a real ORAO program?\n\nReturn the full join_match instruction code and how the tests handle VRF.","agentId":"a43965a69e0c5d654","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information needed. Let me compile the comprehensive report.\n\n## Summary: `join_match` Instruction Analysis\n\n### Full `join_match` Instruction Handler\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/join_match.rs`\n\n```rust\n/// Opponent joins a match, deposits SOL, and requests Orao VRF.\n#[derive(Accounts)]\npub struct JoinMatch<'info> {\n    /// The opponent joining the match. Must sign and fund their escrow.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub opponent: Signer<'info>,\n\n    /// The match PDA to join.\n    #[account(\n        mut,\n        seeds = [b\"match\", coinflip_match.creator.as_ref()],\n        bump = coinflip_match.bump,\n    )]\n    pub coinflip_match: Account<'info, CoinflipMatch>,\n\n    /// The config PDA.\n    #[account(\n        seeds = [b\"coinflip_config\"],\n        bump = config.bump,\n    )]\n    pub config: Account<'info, CoinflipConfig>,\n\n    /// Orao VRF program.\n    /// CHECK: Validated by Orao VRF CPI internally.\n    pub orao_program: UncheckedAccount<'info>,\n\n    /// Orao network state PDA.\n    /// CHECK: Validated by Orao VRF CPI internally.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub orao_network_state: UncheckedAccount<'info>,\n\n    /// Orao treasury for VRF fee payment.\n    /// CHECK: Validated by Orao VRF CPI internally.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub orao_treasury: UncheckedAccount<'info>,\n\n    /// Orao randomness account (created by Orao CPI).\n    /// CHECK: Orao VRF CPI validates and initializes this account.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub orao_random: UncheckedAccount<'info>,\n\n    pub system_program: Program<'info, System>,\n}\n\npub fn handler(ctx: Context<JoinMatch>) -> Result<()> {\n    let coinflip_match = &ctx.accounts.coinflip_match;\n\n    // Validate Waiting → Locked transition via shared lifecycle\n    lifecycle::transition(coinflip_match.phase, RoundPhase::Locked)?;\n\n    // Opponent cannot be the creator\n    require!(\n        ctx.accounts.opponent.key() != coinflip_match.creator,\n        CoinflipError::CannotJoinOwnMatch\n    );\n\n    let entry_amount = coinflip_match.entry_amount;\n    let opponent_key = ctx.accounts.opponent.key();\n\n    // Transfer entry_amount from opponent to match PDA (escrow) via shared helper\n    transfer_lamports_to_pda(\n        &ctx.accounts.opponent.to_account_info(),\n        &ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.to_account_info(),\n        entry_amount,\n        &ctx.accounts.system_program.to_account_info(),\n    )?;\n\n    // Request Orao VRF — use match PDA key as unique seed\n    let seed: [u8; 32] = ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.key().to_bytes();\n    vrf_orao::request_orao_randomness(\n        &ctx.accounts.orao_program.to_account_info(),\n        &ctx.accounts.orao_network_state.to_account_info(),\n        &ctx.accounts.orao_treasury.to_account_info(),\n        &ctx.accounts.orao_random.to_account_info(),\n        &ctx.accounts.opponent.to_account_info(),\n        &ctx.accounts.system_program.to_account_info(),\n        seed,\n    )?;\n\n    // Update match state\n    let now = Clock::get()?.unix_timestamp;\n    let coinflip_match = &mut ctx.accounts.coinflip_match;\n    coinflip_match.opponent = opponent_key;\n    coinflip_match.phase = RoundPhase::Locked;\n    coinflip_match.locked_at = now;\n    coinflip_match.resolve_deadline = now + DEFAULT_RESOLVE_TIMEOUT_SECONDS;\n    coinflip_match.vrf_request_key = ctx.accounts.orao_random.key();\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\n### Accounts Struct Breakdown\n\n| Account | Type | Mutable | Purpose |\n|---------|------|---------|---------|\n| `opponent` | Signer | Yes | The player joining; pays entry amount and signs the tx |\n| `coinflip_match` | PDA (seeds: `[\"match\", creator]`) | Yes | Match state; gets opponent deposited and phase updated |\n| `config` | PDA (seeds: `[\"coinflip_config\"]`) | No | Global config (unused in join_match logic, passed for consistency) |\n| `orao_program` | UncheckedAccount | No | Orao VRF program (CPI target) |\n| `orao_network_state` | UncheckedAccount | Yes | Orao's network state PDA (mutation during VRF CPI) |\n| `orao_treasury` | UncheckedAccount | Yes | Orao's treasury account (receives VRF fee) |\n| `orao_random` | UncheckedAccount | Yes | Orao's randomness account PDA (initialized by Orao CPI) |\n| `system_program` | Program | No | Solana System Program (escrow transfer + VRF CPI) |\n\n### VRF Request Details\n\n**VRF Seed**: The match PDA's public key is used as the seed for the VRF request:\n```rust\nlet seed: [u8; 32] = ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.key().to_bytes();\n```\n\n**VRF Call**: Delegates to shared module `vrf_orao::request_orao_randomness()` which is **feature-gated**:\n\n---\n\n### How Tests Handle VRF (Bankrun + Mock VRF)\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/coinflip.ts`\n\n#### 1. **Mock VRF Setup (Lines 41–55)**\n\nTests define mock randomness buffers instead of relying on real Orao VRF:\n\n```typescript\n// Mock VRF randomness buffers (32 bytes each)\n// HEADS: byte[0]=2 → 2%2=0=HEADS, non-zero so is_fulfilled=true\nconst RANDOMNESS_HEADS = (() => {\n  const buf = Buffer.alloc(32);\n  buf[0] = 2;\n  return buf;\n})();\n\n// TAILS: byte[0]=1 → 1%2=1=TAILS, non-zero so is_fulfilled=true\nconst RANDOMNESS_TAILS = (() => {\n  const buf = Buffer.alloc(32);\n  buf[0] = 1;\n  return buf;\n})();\n\n// Unfulfilled: all zeros → is_fulfilled=false\nconst RANDOMNESS_UNFULFILLED = Buffer.alloc(32);\n```\n\n#### 2. **Mock Orao Accounts Creation (Lines 124–149)**\n\nTest context sets up fake Orao accounts (all with default SystemProgram ownership):\n\n```typescript\nconst mockOraoProgram = Keypair.generate();\nconst mockOraoNetworkState = Keypair.generate();\nconst mockOraoTreasury = Keypair.generate();\nconst mockRandomness = Keypair.generate();\n\nconst context = await startAnchor(\"./\", [], [\n  { address: opponent.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData() },\n  { address: treasury.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData() },\n  // Mock Orao accounts (UncheckedAccount, CPI is no-op under mock-vrf)\n  { address: mockOraoProgram.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData() },\n  { address: mockOraoNetworkState.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData() },\n  { address: mockOraoTreasury.publicKey, info: fundedAccountData() },\n  // Mock randomness account — starts unfulfilled (32 zero bytes)\n  {\n    address: mockRandomness.publicKey,\n    info: {\n      lamports: LAMPORTS_PER_SOL,\n      data: RANDOMNESS_UNFULFILLED,\n      owner: SystemProgram.programId,\n      executable: false,\n    },\n  },\n]);\n```\n\n#### 3. **`joinMatch()` Helper (Lines 258–272)**\n\nTests call `joinMatch()` with the mock Orao accounts:\n\n```typescript\nasync function joinMatch(t: TestContext) {\n  await t.opponentProgram.methods\n    .joinMatch()\n    .accounts({\n      opponent: t.opponent.publicKey,\n      coinflipMatch: t.matchPda,\n      config: t.configPda,\n      oraoProgram: t.mockOraoProgram.publicKey,\n      oraoNetworkState: t.mockOraoNetworkState.publicKey,\n      oraoTreasury: t.mockOraoTreasury.publicKey,\n      oraoRandom: t.mockRandomness.publicKey,\n      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n    })\n    .rpc();\n}\n```\n\n#### 4. **Mock Randomness Setting (Lines 325–332)**\n\nAfter a join, tests manually inject fulfilled randomness into the mock randomness account:\n\n```typescript\nfunction setMockRandomness(t: TestContext, data: Buffer) {\n  t.context.setAccount(t.mockRandomness.publicKey, {\n    lamports: LAMPORTS_PER_SOL,\n    data,\n    owner: SystemProgram.programId,\n    executable: false,\n  });\n}\n\n// Usage in tests:\nsetMockRandomness(t, RANDOMNESS_HEADS);\nsetMockRandomness(t, RANDOMNESS_TAILS);\n```\n\n#### 5. **Feature Flag: `mock-vrf`**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/Cargo.toml`\n\n```toml\n[features]\nno-entrypoint = []\nno-idl = []\nno-log-ix-name = []\ncpi = [\"no-entrypoint\"]\ndefault = [\"mock-vrf\"]  # <-- Tests build with mock-vrf enabled\nmock-vrf = [\"rng-shared/mock-vrf\"]\n```\n\nThis enables the **mock VRF implementation** in the shared crate:\n\n---\n\n### VRF Module Feature-Gated Behavior\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/vrf_orao.rs`\n\n#### Real Mode (`#[cfg(not(feature = \"mock-vrf\"))]`)\n\n```rust\npub fn request_orao_randomness<'info>(\n    orao_program: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    network_state: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    treasury: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    random: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    payer: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    system_program: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    seed: [u8; 32],\n) -> Result<()> {\n    let cpi_accounts = orao_solana_vrf::cpi::accounts::RequestV2 {\n        payer: payer.clone(),\n        network_state: network_state.clone(),\n        treasury: treasury.clone(),\n        request: random.clone(),\n        system_program: system_program.clone(),\n    };\n    let cpi_ctx = CpiContext::new(orao_program.clone(), cpi_accounts);\n    orao_solana_vrf::cpi::request_v2(cpi_ctx, seed)\n}\n```\n\n- **Performs actual CPI** into the real Orao VRF program\n- **RequestV2 CPI**: Initializes the randomness account and deducts fee from payer (opponent)\n- Uses `orao-solana-vrf` crate (`v0.7.0`) with `\"cpi\"` feature\n\n#### Mock Mode (`#[cfg(feature = \"mock-vrf\")]`)\n\n```rust\npub fn request_orao_randomness<'info>(\n    _orao_program: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    _network_state: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    _treasury: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    _random: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    _payer: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    _system_program: &AccountInfo<'info>,\n    _seed: [u8; 32],\n) -> Result<()> {\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\n- **No-op**: CPI is skipped entirely\n- Tests manually inject randomness into the account data (see `setMockRandomness` above)\n- No fee is deducted from payer\n\n#### Randomness Reading (Feature-Gated)\n\n**Real Mode**: Deserializes `orao_solana_vrf::state::RandomnessAccountData` and extracts fulfilled 64-byte randomness\n\n**Mock Mode**: Reads raw 32 bytes directly from account data; checks if any byte is non-zero (is_fulfilled)\n\n---\n\n## Key Findings\n\n1. **No Real Orao Integration in Tests**: Tests use **mock Orao accounts** (dummy keypairs with SystemProgram ownership).\n\n2. **Feature-Gated VRF**: The `mock-vrf` feature flag (enabled by default in Cargo.toml) switches the entire VRF module to no-op CPI and raw byte reading.\n\n3. **VRF Request Seed**: Uses the match PDA public key directly as the 32-byte seed for the Orao VRF request.\n\n4. **Randomness Encoding**: Tests encode coinflip results in the first byte:\n   - `byte[0] % 2 == 0` → HEADS\n   - `byte[0] % 2 == 1` → TAILS\n\n5. **VRF Audit Trail**: The `vrf_request_key` field in `CoinflipMatch` stores the randomness account address for later verification at claim time.\n\n6. **Timeout Fallback**: If VRF doesn't fulfill within `DEFAULT_RESOLVE_TIMEOUT_SECONDS`, either player can refund via `timeout_cancel`."}],"totalDurationMs":44388,"totalTokens":52104,"totalToolUseCount":15,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":381,"cache_read_input_tokens":48118,"output_tokens":3602,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":381,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
