t in the test setup, though the latter would require signing with the deployer keypair.\n\nLet me take a step back and focus on the practical approach: I'll create the account generation script, modify the bootstrap, write the lifecycle test with proper initialization, and handle issues as they come up. Looking at the bankrun test setup, I can see how the initialization flow works with pre-funded accounts and context setup.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":4511,"cache_creation_input_tokens":12708,"cache_read_input_tokens":78208,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":12708},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b0a0dcb3-1758-4eec-aea3-903a9f33143b","uuid":"eaae74f1-6013-4bd2-bdd4-3c4ca22d5e9e"}
